WEBVTT

1
00:00:27.193 --> 00:00:30.544
<font color=#ff00ff>["CRIMSON AND CLOVER" PLAYING
DISTORTEDLY ON RADIO]</font>

2
00:00:37.704 --> 00:00:39.538
<font color=#FF551>ANNOUNCER:</font> <font color=#ff00ff>[ON RADIO]</font> <i>Yes. believe your eyes.</i>

3
00:00:39.539 --> 00:00:42.708
<i>Those are. in fact. the northern
lights on view above the city...</i>

4
00:00:42.709 --> 00:00:44.877
<i>...for the first time in nearly 80 years.</i>

5
00:00:44.878 --> 00:00:46.670
<font color=#ff00ff>[DALE HAWKINS' "SUSIE Q" PLAYING ON RADIO]</font>

6
00:00:46.671 --> 00:00:50.841
<i># Ooh. Susie Q Baby. I love you #</i>

7
00:00:50.842 --> 00:00:52.760
<font color=#FF551>DJ:</font> <font color=#ff00ff>[ON RADIO]</font> <i>It's 5 a.m. Hello. New York.</i>

8
00:00:52.761 --> 00:00:55.471
<i>The big story this morning.
of course. is the Amazins...</i>

9
00:00:55.472 --> 00:00:58.724
<i>...taking the field today in
Baltimore for their final practice...</i>

10
00:00:58.725 --> 00:01:02.102
<i>...before tomorrow's opener of the 1969 World...</i>

11
00:01:02.103 --> 00:01:05.314
<font color=#FF551>ANCHOR:</font> <i>Early this morning. sanitation
workers discovered the dead body...</i>

12
00:01:05.315 --> 00:01:07.608
<i>...of another nurse in a Dumpster in Queens.</i>

13
00:01:07.609 --> 00:01:09.526
<i>This is the third nurse killed...</i>

14
00:01:09.527 --> 00:01:13.072
<i>...in what New York papers are now
calling the Nightingale murders.</i>

15
00:01:13.073 --> 00:01:14.990
<font color=#ff00ff>["CRIMSON AND CLOVER" PLAYING]</font>

16
00:01:14.991 --> 00:01:19.661
<i># What a beautiful feeling #</i>

17
00:01:19.662 --> 00:01:23.040
<font color=#FF551>ANCHOR:</font> <i>All three victims have been
nurses. each of them found strangled...</i>

18
00:01:23.041 --> 00:01:27.377
<i>...with their hands gruesomely bound
behind their backs with glass tape.</i>

19
00:01:27.378 --> 00:01:30.506
<font color=#FF551>ANNOUNCER:</font> <i>The lights. also
known as the aurora borealis...</i>

20
00:01:30.507 --> 00:01:33.399
<font color=#FF551>MAN:</font> Oh. look out!

21
00:01:37.680 --> 00:01:39.348
Oh. my God!

22
00:01:39.349 --> 00:01:41.866
Move it!

23
00:01:46.439 --> 00:01:48.732
<font color=#FF551>DISPATCHER:</font> <i>Manhattan calling Eye of the Storm.</i>

24
00:01:48.733 --> 00:01:51.026
<i>Engine company 12. ladder company 93.</i>

25
00:01:51.027 --> 00:01:56.323
<i>Respond to Manhattan box 132
off-ramp on George Washington Bridge.</i>

26
00:01:56.324 --> 00:01:57.533
We're on our way.

27
00:01:57.534 --> 00:01:59.076
<font color=#FF551>DISPATCHER:</font> <i>Confirm overturned tanker.</i>

28
00:01:59.077 --> 00:02:02.871
<i>Confirm two Con Ed workers trapped in
an underground electric substation.</i>

29
00:02:02.872 --> 00:02:04.915
Frank. we're the second in.

30
00:02:04.916 --> 00:02:07.000
- We got the rescue.
- Great.

31
00:02:07.001 --> 00:02:10.352
<font color=#ff00ff>[SIREN WAILING]</font>

32
00:02:35.738 --> 00:02:37.531
Commander. what do you need done?

33
00:02:37.532 --> 00:02:40.826
That dike's about to go. We're one
spark away from losing the block.

34
00:02:40.827 --> 00:02:44.329
- Is there another way in?
- Only that manhole leads to the vault.

35
00:02:44.330 --> 00:02:45.998
Forget it. Sullivan.

36
00:02:45.999 --> 00:02:50.169
Vault door's rusted shut and
they can't kill the juice.

37
00:02:50.170 --> 00:02:52.296
You won't make it. There's not enough time.

38
00:02:52.297 --> 00:02:55.549
What? Miss the World Series? Not a chance.

39
00:02:55.550 --> 00:02:58.234
Give me my tools.

40
00:03:01.264 --> 00:03:02.931
<font color=#FF551>O'CONNELL:</font> Sullivan. Sullivan.

41
00:03:02.932 --> 00:03:05.726
This is Commander O'Connell. You hear me?

42
00:03:05.727 --> 00:03:07.311
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> I hear you. commander.

43
00:03:07.312 --> 00:03:09.354
<font color=#FF551>O'CONNELL:</font> The gasoline is rising in the vault.

44
00:03:09.355 --> 00:03:12.941
Those downed cables hit
that gas. it's gonna blow.

45
00:03:12.942 --> 00:03:17.753
- Way to go. Gib.
- I should have been a goddamn mailman.

46
00:03:19.866 --> 00:03:23.384
Clear this channel. Explosion's imminent.

47
00:03:28.291 --> 00:03:30.334
Hey. guys. Can you hear me?

48
00:03:30.335 --> 00:03:31.835
<font color=#FF551>- MAN1:</font> We're here.
<font color=#FF551>- FRANK:</font> Coming in.

49
00:03:31.836 --> 00:03:36.981
<font color=#FF551>- MAN1:</font> Come on. get us out of here.
<font color=#FF551>- MAN2:</font> Hey. he's got a broken leg.

50
00:03:38.927 --> 00:03:42.721
Frank. it's gonna flash. Get out of there.

51
00:03:42.722 --> 00:03:44.306
The dike isn't holding.

52
00:03:44.307 --> 00:03:47.184
<font color=#FF551>- MAN1:</font> Get us out!
<font color=#FF551>- BUTCH:</font> Frank. do you hear me?

53
00:03:47.185 --> 00:03:49.228
Yeah. Yeah. I hear you. Butch.

54
00:03:49.229 --> 00:03:52.329
- Grab that axe.
- Here.

55
00:03:52.523 --> 00:03:54.942
Give me a whack. No sparks.

56
00:03:54.943 --> 00:03:56.693
Again.

57
00:03:56.694 --> 00:03:58.487
- One more.
<font color=#FF551>- MAN2:</font> Come on.

58
00:03:58.488 --> 00:04:01.213
Okay. stand back.

59
00:04:10.416 --> 00:04:12.891
<font color=#FF551>MAN1:</font> Oh. thank God.

60
00:04:13.002 --> 00:04:15.212
Hey. my leg's all busted up.

61
00:04:15.213 --> 00:04:18.314
Please. hurry.

62
00:04:18.341 --> 00:04:19.591
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> We're in. Butch.

63
00:04:19.592 --> 00:04:22.094
Right. then get them and get the hell out.

64
00:04:22.095 --> 00:04:25.222
Hey. fellas. Time to go home.

65
00:04:25.223 --> 00:04:27.865
<font color=#FF551>MAN1:</font> Hey. watch it. Watch it.

66
00:04:27.976 --> 00:04:30.686
- It's falling. It's gonna break.
<font color=#FF551>- O'CONNELL:</font> Frank. let's go.

67
00:04:30.687 --> 00:04:33.996
That's an order. Everybody. go.

68
00:04:36.651 --> 00:04:40.654
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> All right. let's move
before the gas lights up.

69
00:04:40.655 --> 00:04:43.365
Watch that wire.

70
00:04:43.366 --> 00:04:45.284
Get out. for chrissake!

71
00:04:45.285 --> 00:04:48.218
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> I got you.

72
00:04:51.708 --> 00:04:55.544
Butch. Butch. we're coming out.
We're coming out right now.

73
00:04:55.545 --> 00:04:57.212
Go!

74
00:04:57.213 --> 00:05:01.065
You all right? Watch your head. Watch your head.

75
00:05:02.051 --> 00:05:04.094
Get up that ladder. Go ahead.

76
00:05:04.095 --> 00:05:07.071
<font color=#FF551>- GIB:</font> Come on. Come on.
- Get up. Get up.

77
00:05:10.435 --> 00:05:12.993
Go on up.

78
00:05:14.147 --> 00:05:15.897
- Go. I'm behind you.
- I'm going.

79
00:05:15.898 --> 00:05:18.734
- Keep going.
- Pull him up.

80
00:05:18.735 --> 00:05:20.277
Come on. Come on. Come on.

81
00:05:20.278 --> 00:05:24.004
Come on. I got you. I got you.

82
00:05:57.648 --> 00:06:01.917
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> Ha. ha. Welcome to the company. Gib.

83
00:06:46.864 --> 00:06:48.198
<font color=#ff00ff>[HORN HONKS]</font>

84
00:06:48.199 --> 00:06:51.049
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> Fellas.

85
00:06:54.705 --> 00:06:57.999
- Hey. Dad.
- Hey. Hey. Gordo.

86
00:06:58.000 --> 00:07:02.519
- Hey. Mr. Sullivan.
- How you doing?

87
00:07:03.589 --> 00:07:05.715
- How's my Little Chief. huh?
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> Good.

88
00:07:05.716 --> 00:07:09.860
<font color=#FF551>- FRANK:</font> Where's your mother?
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> Inside the house.

89
00:07:13.141 --> 00:07:16.492
<font color=#ff00ff>[MARTHA & THE VANDELLAS' "HEAT
WAVE" PLAYING ON RADIO]</font>

90
00:07:17.770 --> 00:07:20.871
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> Hey. Jules.

91
00:07:21.482 --> 00:07:22.691
- Hey. bud.
- Hey. bud.

92
00:07:22.692 --> 00:07:24.025
<font color=#FF551>ANNOUNCER:</font> That was "Heat Wave."

93
00:07:24.026 --> 00:07:27.863
Martha and the Vandellas
here on WOR New York radio.

94
00:07:27.864 --> 00:07:30.615
Hey. how about a little bit of the king. huh?

95
00:07:30.616 --> 00:07:33.743
Yeah. why not a little of the king?

96
00:07:33.744 --> 00:07:35.537
Damn.

97
00:07:35.538 --> 00:07:37.497
- You all right?
- Yeah.

98
00:07:37.498 --> 00:07:40.834
I think I ruined the sauce. Again.

99
00:07:40.835 --> 00:07:42.043
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> What's the matter?

100
00:07:42.044 --> 00:07:43.253
<font color=#ff00ff>[ELVIS' "SUSPICIOUS MINDS" PLAYING]</font>

101
00:07:43.254 --> 00:07:45.714
Having trouble working an
eight-hour shift at the hospital...

102
00:07:45.715 --> 00:07:48.341
...watching the kid. whipping
up a little Bolognese?

103
00:07:48.342 --> 00:07:50.218
<font color=#FF551>JULIA:</font> Didn't marry Donna Reed.

104
00:07:50.219 --> 00:07:56.057
Hey. I'd go for you and Chinese
takeout over her any day.

105
00:07:56.058 --> 00:08:02.788
<font color=#ff00ff>[SINGING]</font> <i># Because I love you too much. baby #</i>

106
00:08:03.941 --> 00:08:05.150
<font color=#ff00ff>[JULIA CHUCKLES]</font>

107
00:08:05.151 --> 00:08:10.363
<i># Why can't you see what you're doing to me? #</i>

108
00:08:10.364 --> 00:08:12.866
- How was your tour?
- The usual. you know.

109
00:08:12.867 --> 00:08:14.075
Butch called.

110
00:08:14.076 --> 00:08:17.052
- Did he?
- He did.

111
00:08:17.413 --> 00:08:19.206
It was under control. bud.

112
00:08:19.207 --> 00:08:22.125
Butch. he's getting a little
tight in his old age.

113
00:08:22.126 --> 00:08:25.462
Nothing wrong with old age.
Frank. long as you get there.

114
00:08:25.463 --> 00:08:29.591
- With suspicious minds
- Suspicious

115
00:08:29.592 --> 00:08:37.682
<i># Baby. we can't build our dreams
On suspicious minds #</i>

116
00:08:37.683 --> 00:08:42.187
<i># So if an old friend I know #</i>

117
00:08:42.188 --> 00:08:46.399
<i># Drops by to say hello #</i>

118
00:08:46.400 --> 00:08:54.965
<i># Would I still see suspicion in your eyes? #</i>

119
00:09:05.503 --> 00:09:08.964
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> All right. Chief. When I let
go. I want you to keep pedaling.

120
00:09:08.965 --> 00:09:11.299
Daddy. put the wheels back on. I'm gonna fall.

121
00:09:11.300 --> 00:09:14.594
Don't worry about falling.
You're ready to do this.

122
00:09:14.595 --> 00:09:18.864
Come on. Spirit and guts. okay?

123
00:09:19.433 --> 00:09:21.935
Okay. All right. keep pedaling.

124
00:09:21.936 --> 00:09:24.646
I'm gonna let go. I'm gonna let go. That's it.

125
00:09:24.647 --> 00:09:27.440
Keep pedaling. Keep pedaling. Keep pedaling.

126
00:09:27.441 --> 00:09:29.317
- Yeah.
- Ow!

127
00:09:29.318 --> 00:09:30.860
You all right?

128
00:09:30.861 --> 00:09:33.795
- You all right?
- Johnny?

129
00:09:34.323 --> 00:09:35.532
You okay?

130
00:09:35.533 --> 00:09:38.285
- You hurt? You okay?
- I wanna go to my room.

131
00:09:38.286 --> 00:09:40.161
<font color=#FF551>JULIA:</font> Okay. go on. honey. It's okay.

132
00:09:40.162 --> 00:09:42.664
Hey. come on. Chief. Don't quit on me now.

133
00:09:42.665 --> 00:09:46.266
Don't be so tough on him.
Frank. He's just a kid.

134
00:09:47.712 --> 00:09:51.104
He just needs to know you're behind him.

135
00:09:52.091 --> 00:09:54.926
Okay. you're right.

136
00:09:54.927 --> 00:09:57.819
All right.

137
00:10:38.929 --> 00:10:42.641
<font color=#FF551>MAN1:</font> <i>CQ-22. this is W2QYV. by for call.</i>

138
00:10:42.642 --> 00:10:44.434
<font color=#FF551>MAN2:</font> <i>It's because of the solar activity.</i>

139
00:10:44.435 --> 00:10:47.729
<font color=#FF551>MAN1:</font> <i>It's beautiful. Got the sky
over my house lit up like a bonfire.</i>

140
00:10:47.730 --> 00:10:49.856
<font color=#FF551>MAN2:</font> <i>Word is sunspots
are shooting off flares...</i>

141
00:10:49.857 --> 00:10:51.900
<i>...that stretch out half a million kilometers.</i>

142
00:10:51.901 --> 00:10:53.234
Look. I've said it before.

143
00:10:53.235 --> 00:10:56.738
<font color=#FF551>MAN1:</font> <i>Tell me about it. I'm picking up
signals in places I could never reach.</i>

144
00:10:56.739 --> 00:10:59.074
<font color=#FF551>MAN3:</font> <i>Francis. is that
you? How are you. my friend?</i>

145
00:10:59.075 --> 00:11:00.950
<font color=#FF551>FRANCIS:</font> <i>I'm doing just great. How you doing?</i>

146
00:11:00.951 --> 00:11:06.596
<font color=#FF551>MAN3:</font> <i>Oh. fantastic. My wife. Sophia.
she's gonna give me another baby.</i>

147
00:11:40.199 --> 00:11:42.617
So that's it. Samantha? You're just walking out?

148
00:11:42.618 --> 00:11:48.346
I've been walking out for six months.
John. You just didn't notice or care.

149
00:11:50.167 --> 00:11:52.919
<font color=#ff00ff>[SOBBING]</font>

150
00:11:52.920 --> 00:11:57.230
You're right. We should've quit a long time ago.

151
00:12:01.053 --> 00:12:02.637
I'm sorry.

152
00:12:02.638 --> 00:12:04.639
I know it's my fault.

153
00:12:04.640 --> 00:12:07.809
I can't change. Sam. I
wish I could. but I can't.

154
00:12:07.810 --> 00:12:12.454
No. John. It's that you won't change.

155
00:12:13.399 --> 00:12:17.042
And that's what hurts so much.

156
00:12:17.945 --> 00:12:21.171
Goodbye. Chief.

157
00:13:12.500 --> 00:13:15.600
<font color=#ff00ff>[CROWD CHEERING IN MEMORY]</font>

158
00:13:16.462 --> 00:13:21.398
<font color=#FF551>ANNOUNCER:</font> <font color=#ff00ff>[VOICE OVER]</font>
Next up. Johnny Sullivan.

159
00:13:22.885 --> 00:13:24.469
<font color=#ff00ff>[BAT CRACKS AND CROWD CHEERS]</font>

160
00:13:24.470 --> 00:13:27.904
It's a hit up the middle.

161
00:13:29.975 --> 00:13:32.868
And Johnny's gonna hold at first.

162
00:13:32.895 --> 00:13:39.040
And now batting for Johnny's
father. Coach Newman.

163
00:13:45.366 --> 00:13:48.243
<font color=#FF551>ANNOUNCER:</font> <font color=#ff00ff>[ON TV]</font> Checks the runner and fires.

164
00:13:48.244 --> 00:13:50.745
Lined hard to right.

165
00:13:50.746 --> 00:13:53.206
No problem. One on. one out.

166
00:13:53.207 --> 00:13:55.333
- Hi. Uncle John.
- I'm not your uncle. kid.

167
00:13:55.334 --> 00:13:57.210
<font color=#FF551>GORDO:</font> Hey. Sully. is that you?

168
00:13:57.211 --> 00:14:00.004
Gordo. what are you guys doing in my house?

169
00:14:00.005 --> 00:14:02.257
My TV's out again.

170
00:14:02.258 --> 00:14:05.927
Hey. uh. you want a brewski?

171
00:14:05.928 --> 00:14:08.096
Yeah.

172
00:14:08.097 --> 00:14:09.639
<font color=#FF551>ANNOUNCER:</font> Deep fly to center field.

173
00:14:09.640 --> 00:14:12.809
<font color=#FF551>GORDO:</font> Can you believe Linda still
won't let me cook in the house?

174
00:14:12.810 --> 00:14:15.186
You know. I melt one lousy frying pan. you know?

175
00:14:15.187 --> 00:14:18.106
John. guess what? Dad's taking me fishing.

176
00:14:18.107 --> 00:14:21.067
- Wanna come?
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> I wish I could. Gordy.

177
00:14:21.068 --> 00:14:23.027
But you bring me back a big one. okay?

178
00:14:23.028 --> 00:14:25.280
Hey. is it okay if Gordy uses your old gear?

179
00:14:25.281 --> 00:14:28.616
Yeah. I think it's somewhere in the
hall closet. if you can find it.

180
00:14:28.617 --> 00:14:30.702
<font color=#FF551>GORDO:</font> Gordy. have a look. huh?

181
00:14:30.703 --> 00:14:32.120
Yeah.

182
00:14:32.121 --> 00:14:35.415
So Yahoo went up another five points today.

183
00:14:35.416 --> 00:14:40.670
- Man. did I miss the boat on that one. huh?
- Should have. would have. could have. pal.

184
00:14:40.671 --> 00:14:43.965
So. Sam called Linda.

185
00:14:43.966 --> 00:14:45.717
<font color=#FF551>GORDY:</font> Dad. John. come here.

186
00:14:45.718 --> 00:14:48.303
<font color=#FF551>GORDO:</font> Gordy. what are
you doing back there. huh?

187
00:14:48.304 --> 00:14:50.889
- Dad. check it out.
- Wow.

188
00:14:50.890 --> 00:14:54.517
Fire Department. Can I open it up?

189
00:14:54.518 --> 00:14:57.452
- Sure.
- Yes.

190
00:15:03.736 --> 00:15:06.988
- Whoa!
- Hey. hey. hey. give me that gun.

191
00:15:06.989 --> 00:15:10.006
All right?

192
00:15:10.993 --> 00:15:14.704
- What's this. Dad?
- Oh. my God.

193
00:15:14.705 --> 00:15:18.499
John. it's your dad's old ham radio.

194
00:15:18.500 --> 00:15:22.211
Remember how we used to beg him
to let us talk on this thing?

195
00:15:22.212 --> 00:15:24.923
- This is not a toy.
- Is not a toy.

196
00:15:24.924 --> 00:15:26.466
<font color=#FF551>GORDY:</font> Well. can we try it. Dad?

197
00:15:26.467 --> 00:15:29.177
- Ask Uncle John.
- Can we try it?

198
00:15:29.178 --> 00:15:30.553
What the hell.

199
00:15:30.554 --> 00:15:32.055
<font color=#FF551>GORDO:</font> All right.

200
00:15:32.056 --> 00:15:34.307
Here. let's grab this baby out.

201
00:15:34.308 --> 00:15:38.353
This is what we used when I was your age.

202
00:15:38.354 --> 00:15:41.981
Let's go over to the den. huh? Plug
it in. just like the old times.

203
00:15:41.982 --> 00:15:44.150
We want CW or LSB.

204
00:15:44.151 --> 00:15:48.237
Stand-by function. Operator. Come on.

205
00:15:48.238 --> 00:15:49.739
I don't know what's going on.

206
00:15:49.740 --> 00:15:52.075
Let's take a look under the hood. huh?

207
00:15:52.076 --> 00:15:55.677
See what we got here.

208
00:15:56.288 --> 00:15:59.916
Check this baby out. There she is.

209
00:15:59.917 --> 00:16:02.710
So this is what people used before the Net. huh?

210
00:16:02.711 --> 00:16:05.505
Well. not exactly. I'll tell you. Hams were...

211
00:16:05.506 --> 00:16:07.006
- Bingo.
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> Yeah.

212
00:16:07.007 --> 00:16:09.926
These babies were different.
Not everybody had one of these.

213
00:16:09.927 --> 00:16:12.637
And you needed a special license
just to be able to talk on them.

214
00:16:12.638 --> 00:16:16.140
- Aw.
- Damn. I just... I just...

215
00:16:16.141 --> 00:16:18.726
- I don't think it's gonna work. kid.
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> It's junk. kid.

216
00:16:18.727 --> 00:16:21.229
Nobody uses those things anymore.

217
00:16:21.230 --> 00:16:24.107
<font color=#FF551>LINDA:</font> Gordo. do you know what time it is?

218
00:16:24.108 --> 00:16:26.275
- Hey. John.
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> Hi. Linda.

219
00:16:26.276 --> 00:16:28.903
Come on. Gordy. Let's go.

220
00:16:28.904 --> 00:16:33.423
I'll catch you later. all right? If I'm lucky.

221
00:16:34.118 --> 00:16:36.744
<i>So feed him.</i>

222
00:16:36.745 --> 00:16:38.830
<i>Put it down there for him.</i>

223
00:16:38.831 --> 00:16:43.584
<i>I'm not gonna... we are not gonna
speak if you continue to say that word.</i>

224
00:16:43.585 --> 00:16:45.670
<font color=#ff00ff>[LINE RINGING]</font>

225
00:16:45.671 --> 00:16:47.588
<font color=#FF551>JULIA:</font> <font color=#ff00ff>[ON RECORDING]</font> <i>This is Julia Sullivan.</i>

226
00:16:47.589 --> 00:16:49.257
<i>Please leave a message after the tone.</i>

227
00:16:49.258 --> 00:16:50.466
<font color=#ff00ff>[ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS]</font>

228
00:16:50.467 --> 00:16:52.510
Hey. Ma. it's me.

229
00:16:52.511 --> 00:16:54.721
Just checking in.

230
00:16:54.722 --> 00:16:56.723
You're probably at work.

231
00:16:56.724 --> 00:16:59.684
Anyways...

232
00:16:59.685 --> 00:17:02.311
...I'll see you tomorrow night.

233
00:17:02.312 --> 00:17:04.814
- I love you.
- <i>She had such fun on her birthdays.</i>

234
00:17:04.815 --> 00:17:07.608
<i>She'd open her present and drift off...</i>

235
00:17:07.609 --> 00:17:11.112
<i>...then look down. see her present
and get happy all over again.</i>

236
00:17:11.113 --> 00:17:15.757
<i>That's what my father does
with his breakfast cereal.</i>

237
00:17:17.745 --> 00:17:20.663
<i>The aurora borealis. to anyone who's seen it...</i>

238
00:17:20.664 --> 00:17:24.292
<i>...is one of the stunning
events of your lifetime.</i>

239
00:17:24.293 --> 00:17:25.793
<i>They're brighter these days.</i>

240
00:17:25.794 --> 00:17:28.713
<i>Is something going on there?
Do they tie in with your field?</i>

241
00:17:28.714 --> 00:17:32.675
- <i>Where do they come from?
- It's a stunning sight. It's beautiful to look at.</i>

242
00:17:32.676 --> 00:17:36.679
<i>I don't think we've seen one
quite this bright for 30 years...</i>

243
00:17:36.680 --> 00:17:39.682
<i>...but from the point of view
of physics and string theory...</i>

244
00:17:39.683 --> 00:17:43.644
<i>...there's nothing really that we gain
from studying the aurora borealis.</i>

245
00:17:43.645 --> 00:17:47.148
<i>History does teach that every time
we thought we had it figured out...</i>

246
00:17:47.149 --> 00:17:50.026
<i>...there was some major discovery
right around the bend...</i>

247
00:17:50.027 --> 00:17:54.363
<i>...that required a complete dramatic change
in our understanding of the laws of physics.</i>

248
00:17:54.364 --> 00:17:57.575
<font color=#FF551>HOST:</font> <i>This is a phrase people have
begun to hear. "string theory."</i>

249
00:17:57.576 --> 00:17:59.285
<font color=#FF551>GREENE:</font> <i>Yes. yes. that's right.</i>

250
00:17:59.286 --> 00:18:03.998
<i>Now. string theory dramatically changes
our understanding of space and time.</i>

251
00:18:03.999 --> 00:18:07.335
<i>For example. it turns out that string
theory requires our universe...</i>

252
00:18:07.336 --> 00:18:09.712
<i>...to have 10 or possibly even 11 dimensions.</i>

253
00:18:09.713 --> 00:18:12.757
<i>Strange thing is some physicists
are even pursuing the idea...</i>

254
00:18:12.758 --> 00:18:15.051
<i>...there might be more than one time dimension.</i>

255
00:18:15.052 --> 00:18:18.429
- <i>Time as we know it. psychological time...
<font color=#ff00ff>- [INDISTINCT CHATTER OVER RADIO]</font></i>

256
00:18:18.430 --> 00:18:20.848
<i>...which seems to organize
events in the universe...</i>

257
00:18:20.849 --> 00:18:22.600
<i>...there may be a second time dimension.</i>

258
00:18:22.601 --> 00:18:27.522
<i>- The universe evolves in a different manner.
<font color=#FF551>- HOST:</font> Another phrase...</i>

259
00:18:27.523 --> 00:18:32.542
<font color=#FF551>MAN:</font> <font color=#ff00ff>[OVER RADIO]</font> <i>CQ-15. CQ-15. come in. 15.</i>

260
00:18:33.112 --> 00:18:35.962
Hello?

261
00:18:36.031 --> 00:18:40.326
<i>Hey. W2QYV here. Who have I got?</i>

262
00:18:40.327 --> 00:18:43.553
Name's John.

263
00:18:44.248 --> 00:18:47.432
You licensed to broadcast. buddy?

264
00:18:47.709 --> 00:18:51.754
Look. I really don't remember
how this thing works.

265
00:18:51.755 --> 00:18:54.715
Listen. you can't broadcast without a license.

266
00:18:54.716 --> 00:18:58.261
Unless this is an emergency. you're
gonna have to get off the band.

267
00:18:58.262 --> 00:19:04.574
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> Pal. my whole life's an emergency.
- Where you transmitting from?

268
00:19:04.810 --> 00:19:06.811
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> Queens. New York.

269
00:19:06.812 --> 00:19:10.314
Well. what do you know?
Bayside. born and raised.

270
00:19:10.315 --> 00:19:13.901
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> No kidding? I thought these things
were for talking around the world.

271
00:19:13.902 --> 00:19:16.654
<font color=#FF551>MAN:</font> Yeah. well. the 15
band closes down at night...

272
00:19:16.655 --> 00:19:21.033
...but during the day. you can chew
the band with China. if you want.

273
00:19:21.034 --> 00:19:23.744
I can't believe people are
still using these things.

274
00:19:23.745 --> 00:19:25.830
You must be a real old-timer. huh?

275
00:19:25.831 --> 00:19:29.292
<font color=#FF551>MAN:</font> Days like this. I feel like
I'm getting there. you know?

276
00:19:29.293 --> 00:19:32.712
So. Queens. uh. you psyched for the Series. huh?

277
00:19:32.713 --> 00:19:37.008
You know. I really don't
follow baseball anymore.

278
00:19:37.009 --> 00:19:39.093
What?

279
00:19:39.094 --> 00:19:42.555
- I just got fed up with all the bullshit.
- What are you talking about?

280
00:19:42.556 --> 00:19:44.015
Let me tell you something.

281
00:19:44.016 --> 00:19:46.851
A thousand years from now when
kids study about America...

282
00:19:46.852 --> 00:19:52.064
...they're gonna learn about three
things: The Constitution. rock 'n' roll...

283
00:19:52.065 --> 00:19:54.609
- ...and baseball.
- Ha-ha-ha.

284
00:19:54.610 --> 00:19:58.571
How can you live in Queens
and not love the Amazins?

285
00:19:58.572 --> 00:20:00.281
The Amazing Mets?

286
00:20:00.282 --> 00:20:03.242
What. the '69 Series?

287
00:20:03.243 --> 00:20:06.829
Man. I'll love Ron Swoboda till the day I die.

288
00:20:06.830 --> 00:20:09.540
<font color=#FF551>MAN:</font> Now I'm with you. He's
got the heart of a lion.

289
00:20:09.541 --> 00:20:12.460
Mets can't win game one without him.

290
00:20:12.461 --> 00:20:15.880
- Can you hear me?
- Game one? What are you talking about?

291
00:20:15.881 --> 00:20:19.592
It was all over after Buford nailed
Seaver's second pitch out of the park.

292
00:20:19.593 --> 00:20:20.968
<font color=#ff00ff>[STATIC BUZZING]</font>

293
00:20:20.969 --> 00:20:23.137
<font color=#FF551>MAN:</font> Hey. no way. buddy. Ain't gonna happen.

294
00:20:23.138 --> 00:20:25.890
Hey. CQ-15? CQ-15. are you there?

295
00:20:25.891 --> 00:20:29.367
<font color=#ff00ff>[STATIC BUZZING]</font>

296
00:20:31.480 --> 00:20:33.522
Who the hell was that?

297
00:20:33.523 --> 00:20:36.317
<font color=#FF551>MAN:</font> Queens. are you there.
Queens? Did I lose you?

298
00:20:36.318 --> 00:20:38.945
Hey. Frank. give the radio a rest.

299
00:20:38.946 --> 00:20:41.530
Your son wants to say good night.

300
00:20:41.531 --> 00:20:43.491
All right. I'll be right there.

301
00:20:43.492 --> 00:20:46.911
<font color=#FF551>HOST:</font> <font color=#ff00ff>[ON TV]</font> <i>Would parallel universes
ever become aware of each other?</i>

302
00:20:46.912 --> 00:20:48.663
<font color=#FF551>GREENE:</font> <i>Who knows? It's a strange idea...</i>

303
00:20:48.664 --> 00:20:49.830
<font color=#ff00ff>[DOG WHIMPERS]</font>

304
00:20:49.831 --> 00:20:51.290
Elvis. you all right? Oh. sorry.

305
00:20:51.291 --> 00:20:52.917
<font color=#FF551>- JULIA:</font> You okay. Frank?
- We're fine.

306
00:20:52.918 --> 00:20:54.877
You all right. buddy?

307
00:20:54.878 --> 00:20:58.506
Oh. you okay. buddy?

308
00:20:58.507 --> 00:21:02.009
<font color=#FF551>GREENE:</font> <i>Not just the aurora. The sunspots
are going to have a serious impact...</i>

309
00:21:02.010 --> 00:21:05.096
<i>...on radio communication for
the next six or seven days.</i>

310
00:21:05.097 --> 00:21:10.017
<i>In fact. quantum theory tells us that the
rigid notions of past. present and future...</i>

311
00:21:10.018 --> 00:21:12.061
<i>...although useful in day-to-day life...</i>

312
00:21:12.062 --> 00:21:15.231
<i>...may dissolve and be replaced
by a complex formulation...</i>

313
00:21:15.232 --> 00:21:19.193
<i>...in which time is far more fluid
than anybody would have imagined.</i>

314
00:21:19.194 --> 00:21:24.115
<font color=#ff00ff>[SINGING]</font> <i># Take me out to the ball game #</i>

315
00:21:24.116 --> 00:21:28.995
<i># Take me out with the crowd #</i>

316
00:21:28.996 --> 00:21:34.375
<i># Buy me some peanuts and Cracker Jacks #</i>

317
00:21:34.376 --> 00:21:39.588
<i># I don't care if I never get back #</i>

318
00:21:39.589 --> 00:21:45.594
<i># 'Cause it's root. root. root for the home team #</i>

319
00:21:45.595 --> 00:21:48.988
<i># If we don't win #</i>

320
00:21:52.352 --> 00:21:55.354
<i># Two. three strikes. you're out #</i>

321
00:21:55.355 --> 00:22:00.735
<i># At the old ball game #</i>

322
00:22:00.736 --> 00:22:03.321
<font color=#FF551>MAN:</font> That's perfect.

323
00:22:03.322 --> 00:22:05.573
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> Butch. you gotta turn the whole set.

324
00:22:05.574 --> 00:22:08.326
<font color=#FF551>BOY:</font> Can't wait till the game.

325
00:22:08.327 --> 00:22:12.345
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> It's not the tuner. It's the antenna.

326
00:22:12.748 --> 00:22:14.790
- Proby.
<font color=#FF551>- PROBY:</font> What?

327
00:22:14.791 --> 00:22:17.543
Point the antenna out from
under the house a little bit.

328
00:22:17.544 --> 00:22:19.378
<font color=#FF551>- PROBY:</font> Like this?
- There. There it is.

329
00:22:19.379 --> 00:22:22.855
- Got it?
- I'll get a beer.

330
00:22:23.008 --> 00:22:26.052
- Hey. hey. hey. Proby. walk away.
<font color=#FF551>- PROBY:</font> Okay. walking away.

331
00:22:26.053 --> 00:22:29.388
<font color=#FF551>- FRANK:</font> If it ain't broke. don't fix it.
<font color=#FF551>- BOY:</font> Come on!

332
00:22:29.389 --> 00:22:32.266
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> Here we go. boys. Here we go.

333
00:22:32.267 --> 00:22:34.268
Hey. Satch. grab a seat. Come on.

334
00:22:34.269 --> 00:22:38.606
Sully. I think I need a new set of cleats.
You know. I lost my footing there.

335
00:22:38.607 --> 00:22:43.527
- Yeah. Yeah. right.
- Dr. DeLeon. you decided to join us.

336
00:22:43.528 --> 00:22:45.488
- You don't wanna know.
- Thank you.

337
00:22:45.489 --> 00:22:47.782
<font color=#FF551>DeLEON:</font> Thirty-six hours. I
was bouncing off the walls.

338
00:22:47.783 --> 00:22:49.950
That's why you're the doctor. I'm the nurse.

339
00:22:49.951 --> 00:22:51.452
- Hey. baby.
- Hey. baby.

340
00:22:51.453 --> 00:22:54.038
- Can I get you something?
- No. no. It's all right.

341
00:22:54.039 --> 00:22:56.665
<font color=#FF551>ANNOUNCER:</font> <i>In left field. Don Buford.</i>

342
00:22:56.666 --> 00:22:58.793
<i>Paul Blair is in center field.</i>

343
00:22:58.794 --> 00:23:00.628
<font color=#FF551>MAN:</font> Sit down.

344
00:23:00.629 --> 00:23:02.630
<font color=#FF551>- SATCH:</font> How you boys doing?
- Good. Satch.

345
00:23:02.631 --> 00:23:04.840
<font color=#FF551>SATCH:</font> Okay. I got something for you.

346
00:23:04.841 --> 00:23:08.010
<font color=#FF551>- ANNOUNCER:</font> Born in Cuba...
- I can't believe it!

347
00:23:08.011 --> 00:23:11.514
<font color=#FF551>- SATCH:</font> And I got something for you.
- Whoa!

348
00:23:11.515 --> 00:23:13.307
Dad. look!

349
00:23:13.308 --> 00:23:17.311
What? You gotta be... hey. are you
Santa Claus or something or what?

350
00:23:17.312 --> 00:23:19.355
- Game three tickets.
<font color=#FF551>- SATCH:</font> Yeah. that's me.

351
00:23:19.356 --> 00:23:21.899
- Did you say "thank you"?
- Thank you. Uncle Satch.

352
00:23:21.900 --> 00:23:24.527
<font color=#FF551>- SATCH:</font> You're welcome.
<font color=#FF551>- FRANK:</font> Thank you. Thank you. Satch.

353
00:23:24.528 --> 00:23:27.905
<font color=#FF551>- SATCH:</font> It's on.
- Hey. all right. Wait. wait. wait.

354
00:23:27.906 --> 00:23:29.532
Everybody.

355
00:23:29.533 --> 00:23:31.117
Everybody say. "Amazing Mets."

356
00:23:31.118 --> 00:23:36.914
<font color=#FF551>ALL:</font> Amazing Mets! Yeah!

357
00:23:36.915 --> 00:23:40.266
<font color=#ff00ff>[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]</font>

358
00:23:53.723 --> 00:23:56.684
Don't choke on your pride. Sul.

359
00:23:56.685 --> 00:23:58.727
You never gonna find another one like Sam.

360
00:23:58.728 --> 00:24:00.187
She made up her mind. Satch.

361
00:24:00.188 --> 00:24:03.524
- Nothing I do is gonna change it.
- Nothing you're willing to do.

362
00:24:03.525 --> 00:24:06.569
- What's the story?
- Construction crew found a body.

363
00:24:06.570 --> 00:24:10.046
Actually. a skeleton.

364
00:24:11.700 --> 00:24:16.495
<font color=#FF551>SATCH:</font> Okay. well. be real
careful when you pull it out.

365
00:24:16.496 --> 00:24:20.040
- Make sure you get the dirt around it.
- Yes. sir. Okay.

366
00:24:20.041 --> 00:24:24.712
<font color=#FF551>- SATCH:</font> So. what's this construction now?
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> I think I'll visit the neighbors. Satch.

367
00:24:24.713 --> 00:24:26.088
Yeah. okay.

368
00:24:26.089 --> 00:24:28.257
- What did they tear down here?
<font color=#FF551>- OFFICER:</font> Greek diner.

369
00:24:28.258 --> 00:24:32.261
<font color=#FF551>MAN:</font> I used to get breakfast there all the time.

370
00:24:32.262 --> 00:24:35.389
Them Greeks were good people.

371
00:24:35.390 --> 00:24:38.017
<font color=#FF551>- MRS. SHEPARD:</font> Careful. It's hot.
- Thank you. Mrs. Shepard.

372
00:24:38.018 --> 00:24:42.897
Once that McDonald's opened up on
Dyckman. they lost all their business.

373
00:24:42.898 --> 00:24:46.901
- I see your son's on the job.
- Was.

374
00:24:46.902 --> 00:24:49.320
Jack died a while back.

375
00:24:49.321 --> 00:24:51.572
It's hard. I know.

376
00:24:51.573 --> 00:24:55.049
It just seems like yesterday.

377
00:24:55.327 --> 00:24:59.246
<font color=#FF551>MR. SHEPARD:</font> My son lived and bled blue.

378
00:24:59.247 --> 00:25:04.642
- Get out of here. Regards to Beth.
<font color=#FF551>- OFFICER:</font> Okay. detective. Sure will.

379
00:25:07.172 --> 00:25:12.525
This isn't gonna be anything but a history
lesson. Let's go back to the house.

380
00:25:25.190 --> 00:25:29.542
- Hey. Barney. How you doing?
- Good.

381
00:25:29.861 --> 00:25:34.463
- Here you go. Thank you.
- Bye.

382
00:25:34.866 --> 00:25:39.620
- I thought it'd be nicer to eat here.
- Hey. sounds good.

383
00:25:39.621 --> 00:25:42.623
I'm sorry Samantha couldn't make it.

384
00:25:42.624 --> 00:25:49.270
Yeah. those grad school applications
are driving her crazy.

385
00:25:49.339 --> 00:25:50.548
How's it coming?

386
00:25:50.549 --> 00:25:53.926
I got the VCR hooked up. It's
just this frigging clock.

387
00:25:53.927 --> 00:25:56.819
Heh. Doesn't matter.

388
00:25:59.224 --> 00:26:04.311
- Damn it. I'm sorry. Mom.
- Hey. I know. It's all right.

389
00:26:04.312 --> 00:26:08.315
- I'm sure everything will work out.
- What's that?

390
00:26:08.316 --> 00:26:09.483
With Sam.

391
00:26:09.484 --> 00:26:13.320
Oh. yeah. you know. just a
tough time right now. you know.

392
00:26:13.321 --> 00:26:17.074
- So how are things at the hospital?
- Fine.

393
00:26:17.075 --> 00:26:21.120
- Hey. Dr. Schwartz retired last month.
- No kidding.

394
00:26:21.121 --> 00:26:25.848
- He must have been pushing 90.
- Close. yeah. Ha-ha-ha.

395
00:26:26.376 --> 00:26:28.752
So how'd you like The Lion King?

396
00:26:28.753 --> 00:26:32.172
Oh. I loved it. Sweet kid. I wish you'd gone.

397
00:26:32.173 --> 00:26:34.800
Yeah. I know. I'm sorry. It's work.

398
00:26:34.801 --> 00:26:37.803
Yeah. you work too hard.

399
00:26:37.804 --> 00:26:41.948
- Look who's talking.
- Ha-ha-ha.

400
00:26:50.108 --> 00:26:55.002
- It's tomorrow.
- Thirty years.

401
00:26:56.906 --> 00:26:59.908
I wish I could remember him better.

402
00:26:59.909 --> 00:27:02.036
<font color=#FF551>JULIA:</font> He was just a big kid.

403
00:27:02.037 --> 00:27:04.872
He wanted to play baseball forever.

404
00:27:04.873 --> 00:27:08.917
And fighting fires. he loved that.

405
00:27:08.918 --> 00:27:11.211
And you.

406
00:27:11.212 --> 00:27:14.772
He loved you.

407
00:27:15.091 --> 00:27:17.343
<font color=#FF551>JULIA:</font> Okay. guys. Bedtime.

408
00:27:17.344 --> 00:27:19.470
Okay. Mom.

409
00:27:19.471 --> 00:27:21.889
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> Looking good. We'll
do it again tomorrow. Chief.

410
00:27:21.890 --> 00:27:25.074
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> Good night. Dad.

411
00:27:27.312 --> 00:27:31.315
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> <font color=#ff00ff>[OVER RADIO]</font> <i>CQ-15. CQ-15.</i>

412
00:27:31.316 --> 00:27:37.780
<i>W2QYV calling unidentified station Queens.</i>

413
00:27:37.781 --> 00:27:40.965
<i>CQ-15?</i>

414
00:27:41.993 --> 00:27:45.913
<i>W2QYV calling unidentified station Queens.</i>

415
00:27:45.914 --> 00:27:49.583
<i>CQ-15. come in. Queens.</i>

416
00:27:49.584 --> 00:27:52.419
Hello.

417
00:27:52.420 --> 00:27:56.924
Hey. hey. is that you? Hey. I've been
trying to cue you all night. Where you been?

418
00:27:56.925 --> 00:28:01.095
Hey. how the hell did you do it?

419
00:28:01.096 --> 00:28:02.721
Do what?

420
00:28:02.722 --> 00:28:04.473
Do what? The Series.

421
00:28:04.474 --> 00:28:07.768
You called Buford's homer.
How the hell did you do it?

422
00:28:07.769 --> 00:28:11.188
It wasn't too tough. buddy.
The game happened 30 years ago.

423
00:28:11.189 --> 00:28:14.108
Yeah. right. right. Yeah.
30 years ago. Yeah. sure.

424
00:28:14.109 --> 00:28:16.777
I suppose you could tell me
what happened in game two.

425
00:28:16.778 --> 00:28:20.948
Yeah. sure. Top of the ninth. Al
Weis. game-winning RBI single.

426
00:28:20.949 --> 00:28:24.284
<font color=#ff00ff>[OVER RADIO]</font> Brooks Robinson
grounds out to end the game.

427
00:28:24.285 --> 00:28:26.745
Daddy. come up and sing the baseball song.

428
00:28:26.746 --> 00:28:29.790
Hey. Little Chief. You all right?

429
00:28:29.791 --> 00:28:32.334
Okay. you just go on up.
I'll be there in a minute.

430
00:28:32.335 --> 00:28:35.644
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> Okay.
<font color=#FF551>- FRANK:</font> All right.

431
00:28:36.131 --> 00:28:38.841
- Sorry about that. That was my kid.
- What'd you say?

432
00:28:38.842 --> 00:28:40.926
Sorry about that. My kid just came in.

433
00:28:40.927 --> 00:28:43.762
You call your son Little Chief?

434
00:28:43.763 --> 00:28:45.681
Yeah.

435
00:28:45.682 --> 00:28:48.559
What did you say your name was?

436
00:28:48.560 --> 00:28:50.936
Frank. Frank Sullivan.

437
00:28:50.937 --> 00:28:52.771
Is this some kind of joke?

438
00:28:52.772 --> 00:28:55.399
Gordo. is that you? Are you messing with me?

439
00:28:55.400 --> 00:28:57.776
I ain't messing with you.
I'm trying to figure...

440
00:28:57.777 --> 00:29:01.113
You're telling me your name is Frank
Sullivan. you live in Queens...

441
00:29:01.114 --> 00:29:06.118
...and you wanna know how I called the
first game of the 1969 World Series?

442
00:29:06.119 --> 00:29:10.038
- Yeah. that's exactly what I wanna know.
- Ha-ha-ha.

443
00:29:10.039 --> 00:29:14.168
Gordo. if this is you. so help me...

444
00:29:14.169 --> 00:29:15.502
- What'd you say...?
- Gordo?

445
00:29:15.503 --> 00:29:21.508
What'd you say your call station
or your call letters were?

446
00:29:21.509 --> 00:29:25.820
W2QYV.

447
00:29:27.891 --> 00:29:29.683
Now you listen to me.

448
00:29:29.684 --> 00:29:32.019
My name is John Francis Sullivan.

449
00:29:32.020 --> 00:29:36.231
I live at 34342nd Avenue.
where I lived my whole life.

450
00:29:36.232 --> 00:29:39.943
And I saw the first game
of the 1969 World Series...

451
00:29:39.944 --> 00:29:43.071
- ...right here in this house 30 years ago.
- Bullshit.

452
00:29:43.072 --> 00:29:46.283
My father's name is Francis Patrick Sullivan.

453
00:29:46.284 --> 00:29:49.369
He was a firefighter and a die-hard Mets fan.

454
00:29:49.370 --> 00:29:51.622
- Every night when I went to bed...
- Bullshit.

455
00:29:51.623 --> 00:29:56.016
...he sang to me. "Take Me Out to the Ballgame."

456
00:29:59.255 --> 00:30:02.174
Hey. who the hell are you?

457
00:30:02.175 --> 00:30:04.733
Son of a bitch.

458
00:30:05.678 --> 00:30:09.572
- What's going on?
- <i>Nothing. Nothing's going on.</i>

459
00:30:15.480 --> 00:30:16.855
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> Oh. my God.

460
00:30:16.856 --> 00:30:20.317
<i>You burned the desk. I can see it.</i>

461
00:30:20.318 --> 00:30:22.194
<i>Are you still there?</i>

462
00:30:22.195 --> 00:30:24.905
<i>I said. you burned the desk. I can see it.</i>

463
00:30:24.906 --> 00:30:26.615
<i>Hello.</i>

464
00:30:26.616 --> 00:30:29.409
<i>Hello. Are you still there?</i>

465
00:30:29.410 --> 00:30:32.329
<i>Come back. Talk to me.</i>

466
00:30:32.330 --> 00:30:36.959
Hello. Hey. hello?

467
00:30:36.960 --> 00:30:40.379
Hey. hey. listen to me.
You listen to me right now.

468
00:30:40.380 --> 00:30:42.840
I don't know who you are
or why you're doing this.

469
00:30:42.841 --> 00:30:45.008
Let me tell you something. asshole.

470
00:30:45.009 --> 00:30:47.427
You stay away from me and my family.

471
00:30:47.428 --> 00:30:50.430
No. no. no. You gotta believe me.

472
00:30:50.431 --> 00:30:54.518
I don't know how this is happening.
but it's me. Little Chief.

473
00:30:54.519 --> 00:30:57.271
Hey. hey. hey. look. look. I am warning you.

474
00:30:57.272 --> 00:31:02.708
If you touch my kid. I will hunt you
down till the day I die. You got that?

475
00:31:03.361 --> 00:31:04.987
But you already died.

476
00:31:04.988 --> 00:31:06.780
What are you talking about?

477
00:31:06.781 --> 00:31:09.924
The Buxton fire.

478
00:31:09.951 --> 00:31:12.744
Oh. yeah? And when did
that happen. 30 years ago?

479
00:31:12.745 --> 00:31:15.247
October 12. 1969.

480
00:31:15.248 --> 00:31:16.915
Tomorrow. I'm gonna die...

481
00:31:16.916 --> 00:31:20.252
I ain't dying in no fire tomorrow
or any other day. You got that?

482
00:31:20.253 --> 00:31:23.505
- Tomorrow hasn't happened.
- It hasn't happened. Ain't gonna happen.

483
00:31:23.506 --> 00:31:26.091
No. you listen to me. It
was an abandoned warehouse.

484
00:31:26.092 --> 00:31:29.261
Butch told Ma it wasn't your fault.
You went with your instincts.

485
00:31:29.262 --> 00:31:31.138
- I'm warning you.
- If you'd gone the other...

486
00:31:31.139 --> 00:31:32.389
<font color=#ff00ff>[STATIC BUZZING]</font>

487
00:31:32.390 --> 00:31:37.144
If you'd just gone the other way.
you would have made it. Hello?

488
00:31:37.145 --> 00:31:40.120
<font color=#ff00ff>[DISTORTED]</font> <i>Hello... Hello.</i>

489
00:31:44.569 --> 00:31:48.462
Hello. Shit.

490
00:32:16.517 --> 00:32:19.102
<font color=#FF551>GORDO:</font> Sully. what are you doing. man?

491
00:32:19.103 --> 00:32:21.980
I talked to him. Gordo. I talked to my dad.

492
00:32:21.981 --> 00:32:25.525
<font color=#FF551>GORDO:</font> Sully. go in the house. all
right? I'll come over and we'll hang out.

493
00:32:25.526 --> 00:32:29.029
No. no. no. I gotta get him
back so he doesn't go in.

494
00:32:29.030 --> 00:32:30.864
Go in? What do you...? Go in where?

495
00:32:30.865 --> 00:32:34.717
The warehouse in Buxton. It's tomorrow.

496
00:32:49.926 --> 00:32:53.679
<font color=#ff00ff>[THINKING]</font> Yeah. right. right.
Yeah. 30 years ago. Yeah. sure.

497
00:32:53.680 --> 00:32:56.765
So I suppose you could tell me
what happened in game two. huh?

498
00:32:56.766 --> 00:33:02.396
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> <i>Yeah. sure. Top of the ninth.
Al Weis. game-winning RBI single.</i>

499
00:33:02.397 --> 00:33:04.856
<font color=#FF551>- MAN1:</font> Come on.
<font color=#FF551>- MAN2:</font> Hit it. Al.

500
00:33:04.857 --> 00:33:07.109
- Warm it up.
- That's good. That's good. yeah.

501
00:33:07.110 --> 00:33:10.044
Look at the stats. Look at them.

502
00:33:10.697 --> 00:33:12.739
<font color=#FF551>MAN1:</font> Let's go. Weis.

503
00:33:12.740 --> 00:33:15.409
<font color=#FF551>ALL:</font> Yeah!

504
00:33:15.410 --> 00:33:18.761
<font color=#ff00ff>[ALARM BLARING]</font>

505
00:33:18.871 --> 00:33:21.581
<font color=#FF551>DISPATCHER:</font> We have a
three-and-two response. Ladder 93.

506
00:33:21.582 --> 00:33:25.711
You're first due. It's reported
to be an abandoned warehouse...

507
00:33:25.712 --> 00:33:27.713
...at the foot of Water Street and 3rd.

508
00:33:27.714 --> 00:33:33.093
- You got some construction. limited access.
<font color=#FF551>- ANNOUNCER:</font> Weis is having a great series.

509
00:33:33.094 --> 00:33:36.445
<font color=#ff00ff>[SIRENS WAILING]</font>

510
00:33:44.355 --> 00:33:47.706
<font color=#ff00ff>[ANNOUNCER SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ON RADIO]</font>

511
00:33:56.451 --> 00:33:59.635
Yeah. we won!

512
00:34:00.455 --> 00:34:04.973
Frank. you all right?

513
00:34:31.027 --> 00:34:33.028
<font color=#FF551>BUTCH:</font> We know it's vacant.

514
00:34:33.029 --> 00:34:36.797
Nobody goes in. Surround and drown.

515
00:34:39.494 --> 00:34:42.621
Call for a tower.

516
00:34:42.622 --> 00:34:46.083
<font color=#FF551>- WOMAN:</font> Help!
- Shit. we got squatters inside.

517
00:34:46.084 --> 00:34:48.559
Help!

518
00:34:50.129 --> 00:34:51.838
Help! Help!

519
00:34:51.839 --> 00:34:53.673
- My sister.
- Whoa. whoa. whoa!

520
00:34:53.674 --> 00:34:55.509
She's up there. She passed out.

521
00:34:55.510 --> 00:34:58.178
- Where's your sister? What floor?
- I tried to help.

522
00:34:58.179 --> 00:35:01.014
- Tell me what floor.
- She's up there on the top floor.

523
00:35:01.015 --> 00:35:03.517
<i>I tried. I tried.</i>

524
00:35:03.518 --> 00:35:05.477
Please. help her. Please.

525
00:35:05.478 --> 00:35:07.104
Butch. take her. Come on. proby.

526
00:35:07.105 --> 00:35:08.396
- Anybody else there?
- No.

527
00:35:08.397 --> 00:35:11.748
<font color=#ff00ff>[BOAT HORN HONKING]</font>

528
00:35:19.700 --> 00:35:24.052
Ryan. get her medical treatment.

529
00:35:34.382 --> 00:35:38.734
<font color=#FF551>- FRANK:</font> Give me my gear.
<font color=#FF551>- MAN:</font> <font color=#ff00ff>[OVER RADIO]</font> Fire on the top floor.

530
00:35:40.888 --> 00:35:43.181
- Hey. Sul.
- Satch.

531
00:35:43.182 --> 00:35:45.267
Hey. here he is.

532
00:35:45.268 --> 00:35:47.227
So how you feeling. Sul?

533
00:35:47.228 --> 00:35:48.812
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> What can I tell you?

534
00:35:48.813 --> 00:35:50.355
<font color=#FF551>- WOMAN:</font> Here you go.
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> Thanks.

535
00:35:50.356 --> 00:35:53.165
Better.

536
00:35:59.240 --> 00:36:03.634
No visible fire. first or second floor.

537
00:36:05.121 --> 00:36:09.556
Watch your step. proby. This floor's rotten.

538
00:36:12.753 --> 00:36:15.964
<font color=#ff00ff>[OVER RADIO]</font> Got fire on the third floor.
Need a line in place. We're going up.

539
00:36:15.965 --> 00:36:18.941
We got two lines coming behind you.

540
00:36:43.910 --> 00:36:46.328
- Back out. Wait for the line.
- Hell with the line.

541
00:36:46.329 --> 00:36:50.472
- I'll find another way up.
- No. you can't help me here.

542
00:37:04.138 --> 00:37:07.990
<font color=#FF551>DISPATCHER:</font> We don't need it
right now. Just be prepared.

543
00:37:20.029 --> 00:37:21.863
So you doing okay. John?

544
00:37:21.864 --> 00:37:26.174
Yeah. Tough day. you know.

545
00:37:29.497 --> 00:37:32.457
Hey. here's to your dad. huh?

546
00:37:32.458 --> 00:37:35.919
- Thirty years today.
- To your dad.

547
00:37:35.920 --> 00:37:39.021
To my dad.

548
00:37:43.511 --> 00:37:47.654
We're pulling everyone out of the building.

549
00:37:52.603 --> 00:37:56.022
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> Get that to the top
floor. It's cooking up here.

550
00:37:56.023 --> 00:37:59.901
So after that Halloween thing with
the fire truck. you remember that?

551
00:37:59.902 --> 00:38:02.529
I remember riding around
with Butch and your dad.

552
00:38:02.530 --> 00:38:08.118
- The whole neighborhood was watching.
- I remember. I wanted to go as a cop then.

553
00:38:08.119 --> 00:38:12.414
Yeah. so then Jules makes your dad buy
you that cop kit for your birthday.

554
00:38:12.415 --> 00:38:14.207
Oh. I remember that.

555
00:38:14.208 --> 00:38:16.710
I was always the robber.
always being handcuffed.

556
00:38:16.711 --> 00:38:19.713
<font color=#FF551>SATCH:</font> That's right. I taught you to do that.

557
00:38:19.714 --> 00:38:23.065
<font color=#ff00ff>[WOOD CLATTERING AND FIRE BLAZING]</font>

558
00:38:23.134 --> 00:38:26.485
<font color=#ff00ff>[COUGHING]</font>

559
00:38:45.906 --> 00:38:48.241
10:45. I found the girl.

560
00:38:48.242 --> 00:38:51.843
- <i>She's breathing.</i>
- Get them out.

561
00:38:57.835 --> 00:39:00.227
Go!

562
00:39:02.506 --> 00:39:04.257
Hang on.

563
00:39:04.258 --> 00:39:07.093
What the hell is going on?

564
00:39:07.094 --> 00:39:11.514
- Gino. what's the matter?
- The gear box. it's cracked.

565
00:39:11.515 --> 00:39:13.600
<font color=#FF551>BUTCH:</font> Frank. Frank. that ladder's jammed.

566
00:39:13.601 --> 00:39:17.354
That ladder's jammed. Frank.
you gotta find another way out.

567
00:39:17.355 --> 00:39:20.080
Frank. can you hear me?

568
00:39:32.536 --> 00:39:34.746
It worked out okay. though.

569
00:39:34.747 --> 00:39:38.124
You're a better cop than a
fireman. No doubt about it.

570
00:39:38.125 --> 00:39:39.959
<font color=#FF551>GORDO:</font> Worked out good for me too.

571
00:39:39.960 --> 00:39:42.670
I'm glad I never spent 10 years as his hose man.

572
00:39:42.671 --> 00:39:43.922
<font color=#FF551>SATCH:</font> Yeah. I bet you are.

573
00:39:43.923 --> 00:39:45.340
Yeah. I bet you are.

574
00:39:45.341 --> 00:39:48.692
<font color=#ff00ff>[CHUCKLING]</font>

575
00:39:50.429 --> 00:39:52.847
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> <font color=#ff00ff>[VOICE OVER]</font> <i>The Buxton
fire. It wasn't your fault.</i>

576
00:39:52.848 --> 00:39:55.782
<i>If you had just gone the other way...</i>

577
00:40:04.944 --> 00:40:08.003
<font color=#FF551>ALL:</font> Cheers!

578
00:40:18.374 --> 00:40:23.268
- Frank. we're losing the building.
- I know.

579
00:40:54.118 --> 00:40:56.885
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> <i>Hey. hey. hey. This is not...</i>

580
00:41:04.920 --> 00:41:08.230
- Hey.
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> Daddy.

581
00:41:15.973 --> 00:41:18.782
Blue.

582
00:41:20.728 --> 00:41:23.161
Relax. Chief.

583
00:41:30.821 --> 00:41:34.047
Hey. hey. hey. This is not a toy.

584
00:41:38.204 --> 00:41:41.638
Hey. you wanna play?

585
00:41:45.127 --> 00:41:48.603
- Wave to Ma.
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> Mom. look at us.

586
00:41:56.931 --> 00:41:59.906
Thank you all.

587
00:42:02.895 --> 00:42:05.787
You're gonna be some ballplayer.

588
00:42:18.077 --> 00:42:20.787
<font color=#FF551>WOMAN:</font> Whoa. hey. careful.

589
00:42:20.788 --> 00:42:22.288
John. you all right?

590
00:42:22.289 --> 00:42:23.915
John. John.

591
00:42:23.916 --> 00:42:26.000
- I'm sorry.
<font color=#FF551>- GORDO:</font> What is it?

592
00:42:26.001 --> 00:42:30.020
- Is everything okay?
- Yeah. can you just bring us a towel?

593
00:42:46.146 --> 00:42:47.855
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> Get her up.

594
00:42:47.856 --> 00:42:51.150
- Satch. my father didn't die in a fire. right?
<font color=#FF551>- SATCH:</font> Huh?

595
00:42:51.151 --> 00:42:54.252
Gordo. my father didn't die in a fire.

596
00:42:56.323 --> 00:42:59.007
<font color=#FF551>MAN:</font> Easy.

597
00:42:59.118 --> 00:43:02.886
What are you talking about. John? He had cancer.

598
00:43:07.501 --> 00:43:10.044
Cancer. because it was the cigarettes. right?

599
00:43:10.045 --> 00:43:13.438
Yeah. lung cancer. 10 years ago.

600
00:43:23.517 --> 00:43:25.685
Little Chief.

601
00:43:25.686 --> 00:43:29.955
Gordo. I ain't dreaming here.
I talked to him. It was real.

602
00:43:30.149 --> 00:43:32.358
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> Little Chief! Ha-ha-ha.

603
00:43:32.359 --> 00:43:35.028
<font color=#FF551>GORDO:</font> What are you talking about?

604
00:43:35.029 --> 00:43:39.907
It was a ham radio. That's how
come he didn't die. you know.

605
00:43:39.908 --> 00:43:44.260
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> Little Chief! Ha-ha-ha.

606
00:43:45.289 --> 00:43:48.223
<font color=#ff00ff>[CHUCKLES]</font>

607
00:43:49.335 --> 00:43:52.712
That's how come he didn't die.

608
00:43:52.713 --> 00:43:57.175
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> John. John Sullivan. are you there?

609
00:43:57.176 --> 00:44:00.443
Come on. answer me.

610
00:44:02.431 --> 00:44:06.059
Chief. Chief. are you there?

611
00:44:06.060 --> 00:44:09.411
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> I'm right here. Daddy.

612
00:44:09.688 --> 00:44:12.523
Come here.

613
00:44:12.524 --> 00:44:15.291
Come on.

614
00:44:18.238 --> 00:44:20.531
- Where's Elvis?
- Sleeping.

615
00:44:20.532 --> 00:44:22.325
Sleeping. Why aren't you sleeping?

616
00:44:22.326 --> 00:44:26.094
- You woke me up.
- I did?

617
00:44:28.248 --> 00:44:33.059
- Hey. I got an idea.
- What's that?

618
00:44:35.464 --> 00:44:38.857
All right. Chief.

619
00:44:39.093 --> 00:44:41.511
What do you say we tame this bronco. huh?

620
00:44:41.512 --> 00:44:45.932
- I'm scared.
- I know. And you know what?

621
00:44:45.933 --> 00:44:50.228
I'm gonna be right here with you. always.

622
00:44:50.229 --> 00:44:52.605
Daddy. I can't.

623
00:44:52.606 --> 00:44:55.942
Well. we can. We can do it together.

624
00:44:55.943 --> 00:44:59.612
You and me. Spirit and guts. What do you say?

625
00:44:59.613 --> 00:45:03.491
- Okay.
- All right. Come on.

626
00:45:03.492 --> 00:45:06.619
Now. you just take your time.

627
00:45:06.620 --> 00:45:09.122
I'm not gonna let go until you say it's okay.

628
00:45:09.123 --> 00:45:10.498
- Okay.
- All right?

629
00:45:10.499 --> 00:45:12.917
All right. start pedaling.

630
00:45:12.918 --> 00:45:15.545
That's it. Get your balance.

631
00:45:15.546 --> 00:45:16.754
- Ready?
- Wait.

632
00:45:16.755 --> 00:45:18.673
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> Okay. okay. I'm still here.

633
00:45:18.674 --> 00:45:20.508
- Okay.
- All right.

634
00:45:20.509 --> 00:45:21.968
- It's all you.
- Look at me.

635
00:45:21.969 --> 00:45:24.470
It's all you. It's all you. Chief.

636
00:45:24.471 --> 00:45:26.305
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> Look at me. Dad.
- Hey. look at you.

637
00:45:26.306 --> 00:45:29.183
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> I'm doing it. I'm doing it.
- You're doing it. Look at you.

638
00:45:29.184 --> 00:45:31.936
- You're doing it.
- I'm doing it.

639
00:45:31.937 --> 00:45:35.481
<font color=#FF551>- FRANK:</font> <i>How's it feel?
- Good.</i>

640
00:45:35.482 --> 00:45:39.527
<font color=#FF551>- FRANK:</font> <i>Look at you. like a circus act.
- This is great. like a flying trapeze.</i>

641
00:45:39.528 --> 00:45:41.404
<font color=#FF551>- FRANK:</font> <i>Look at you.
- This feels great.</i>

642
00:45:41.405 --> 00:45:43.823
<font color=#FF551>- FRANK:</font> <i>You're going around the world.
- It's like flying.</i>

643
00:45:43.824 --> 00:45:46.909
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> <i>Wait till your mother sees this. huh?</i>

644
00:45:46.910 --> 00:45:50.246
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> <i>Look at me.
- Let's wake up the world. huh?</i>

645
00:45:50.247 --> 00:45:53.598
<font color=#ff00ff>[FRANK LAUGHING]</font>

646
00:46:31.791 --> 00:46:37.183
Oh. my God... oh. my God.

647
00:47:19.044 --> 00:47:21.853
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> <font color=#ff00ff>[OVER RADIO]</font> <i>Hello?</i>

648
00:47:24.049 --> 00:47:27.468
- <i>Hello?</i>
- John?

649
00:47:27.469 --> 00:47:30.486
John Sullivan?

650
00:47:31.682 --> 00:47:34.532
It's me.

651
00:47:43.569 --> 00:47:46.112
<i>You're the voice of an angel.</i>

652
00:47:46.113 --> 00:47:51.534
<i>Reached right out of heaven and
you pulled my butt out of the fire.</i>

653
00:47:51.535 --> 00:47:55.955
Tell me I'm not dreaming
here. Tell me it's really you.

654
00:47:55.956 --> 00:47:58.541
<i>It's me. John.</i>

655
00:47:58.542 --> 00:48:00.877
<i>This ain't no dream.</i>

656
00:48:00.878 --> 00:48:03.504
- But how could it be?
- I don't know. I don't know.

657
00:48:03.505 --> 00:48:06.966
But we gotta be talking off
the mother sunspot of all time.

658
00:48:06.967 --> 00:48:08.509
<i>Yeah. I'd say so.</i>

659
00:48:08.510 --> 00:48:11.861
<font color=#ff00ff>[CHUCKLING]</font>

660
00:48:12.890 --> 00:48:15.474
You okay. Chief?

661
00:48:15.475 --> 00:48:18.060
Yeah. I'm fine.

662
00:48:18.061 --> 00:48:20.313
<i>You sure?</i>

663
00:48:20.314 --> 00:48:23.065
Uh. it's. uh...

664
00:48:23.066 --> 00:48:26.986
Heh. it's. uh. tough to explain.

665
00:48:26.987 --> 00:48:32.617
I mean. I've got all these new memories.
but it's like I don't know what to believe.

666
00:48:32.618 --> 00:48:34.118
What do you mean?

667
00:48:34.119 --> 00:48:37.496
<i>Because I still remember what it
was like when you died in the fire.</i>

668
00:48:37.497 --> 00:48:39.832
<i>But I'm the only one.</i>

669
00:48:39.833 --> 00:48:43.434
I don't understand what you're talking about.

670
00:48:43.587 --> 00:48:46.130
I remember both at the same time.

671
00:48:46.131 --> 00:48:50.843
And it's like waking up from a dream
and you're not sure what's real.

672
00:48:50.844 --> 00:48:54.847
I remember you being here. but I
also remember when you weren't.

673
00:48:54.848 --> 00:48:57.725
Oh. I'm sorry. John.

674
00:48:57.726 --> 00:49:02.188
- I'm sorry. I never thought that...
- <i>Well. you gotta think about that.</i>

675
00:49:02.189 --> 00:49:05.775
And you gotta be more careful.
because I can't lose you again.

676
00:49:05.776 --> 00:49:08.459
Not like that.

677
00:49:10.072 --> 00:49:12.323
You won't. John. You won't.

678
00:49:12.324 --> 00:49:15.284
I swear to God. no matter what. not like that.

679
00:49:15.285 --> 00:49:17.870
You got it? You hear me?

680
00:49:17.871 --> 00:49:19.538
<i>You hear me. Chief?</i>

681
00:49:19.539 --> 00:49:22.432
I hear you.

682
00:49:26.213 --> 00:49:29.772
So how old are you?

683
00:49:30.467 --> 00:49:32.969
Ahem. I'm 36.

684
00:49:32.970 --> 00:49:35.429
<i>Thirty-six?</i>

685
00:49:35.430 --> 00:49:37.848
You're all grown up. Ha. ha.

686
00:49:37.849 --> 00:49:40.226
You gotta be married and everything.

687
00:49:40.227 --> 00:49:43.229
<i>No. I'm not married.</i>

688
00:49:43.230 --> 00:49:47.900
- What. you're too busy playing ball?
- <i>No.</i>

689
00:49:47.901 --> 00:49:51.278
<i>It didn't work out. I gave it up.</i>

690
00:49:51.279 --> 00:49:52.947
What happened?

691
00:49:52.948 --> 00:49:59.203
I just blew my arm out my senior
year and didn't have a shot.

692
00:49:59.204 --> 00:50:03.332
Oh. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
Johnny. I know that had to hurt.

693
00:50:03.333 --> 00:50:07.003
<i>Yeah. thanks.</i>

694
00:50:07.004 --> 00:50:11.105
So. what did you wind up
doing? You join the department?

695
00:50:12.342 --> 00:50:14.969
Actually. I went the other way.

696
00:50:14.970 --> 00:50:16.762
I'm a cop.

697
00:50:16.763 --> 00:50:18.389
<font color=#ff00ff>[BOTH CHUCKLING]</font>

698
00:50:18.390 --> 00:50:22.601
You're third-generation firefighter. I
thought you'd grow out of that cop phase.

699
00:50:22.602 --> 00:50:24.854
<i>Well. you got Satch to thank for that one.</i>

700
00:50:24.855 --> 00:50:26.981
<i>You gotta be kidding me. huh?</i>

701
00:50:26.982 --> 00:50:33.503
<i>Satch. he always crazy about
you ever since you were born.</i>

702
00:50:35.907 --> 00:50:38.951
You're still my Little Chief.

703
00:50:38.952 --> 00:50:41.328
Right?

704
00:50:41.329 --> 00:50:44.138
<i>Right?</i>

705
00:50:44.458 --> 00:50:50.144
Yeah. I'm trying to be. I'm trying.

706
00:50:52.883 --> 00:50:55.634
Well. tell me about yourself.

707
00:50:55.635 --> 00:50:57.470
Tell me about your life.

708
00:50:57.471 --> 00:51:02.308
I mean. uh. where do I start. you know?

709
00:51:02.309 --> 00:51:05.311
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> <i>Mustang? I don't own a Mustang.</i>

710
00:51:05.312 --> 00:51:08.189
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> <i>Well. you will and you loved it.</i>

711
00:51:08.190 --> 00:51:10.316
- Fire-engine red. Four on the floor.
- Yeah?

712
00:51:10.317 --> 00:51:13.527
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> <i>Seventy home runs? That's a
record that will never be broken.</i>

713
00:51:13.528 --> 00:51:16.864
I wouldn't be too sure. The other guy hit 66.

714
00:51:16.865 --> 00:51:20.701
Really? You mean like those big
field radios they use in the Army?

715
00:51:20.702 --> 00:51:25.706
Smaller. Works off a satellite or something.
You carry it around in your pocket.

716
00:51:25.707 --> 00:51:29.335
Hey. what about Apollo? How'd it all work out?

717
00:51:29.336 --> 00:51:31.504
It was a great series. Pop. Amazing.

718
00:51:31.505 --> 00:51:34.673
- So we win. right?
- Hold your horses. I'm getting there.

719
00:51:34.674 --> 00:51:38.177
Game three. Agee came through.
homered off Palmer in the second.

720
00:51:38.178 --> 00:51:40.846
I knew it. I knew Agee was
gonna have a great series.

721
00:51:40.847 --> 00:51:45.017
Forget about Agee. Wait until you
hear what happened to Cleon Jones.

722
00:51:45.018 --> 00:51:47.269
- Now you sound like your mother.
- I'm serious.

723
00:51:47.270 --> 00:51:50.523
Oh. come on. Your grandfather. he
smoked. what. two packs a day...

724
00:51:50.524 --> 00:51:53.526
- ...and he's still kicking.
- <i>Not you.</i>

725
00:51:53.527 --> 00:51:57.044
It's gonna get the better of you.

726
00:51:58.824 --> 00:52:01.283
Okay?

727
00:52:01.284 --> 00:52:04.245
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> <i>Well. I just knew.</i>

728
00:52:04.246 --> 00:52:08.124
<i>She melted my heart. That was it.</i>

729
00:52:08.125 --> 00:52:10.376
<i>You got anybody?</i>

730
00:52:10.377 --> 00:52:15.047
Yeah. kind of.

731
00:52:15.048 --> 00:52:19.108
Something I gotta work out. but...

732
00:52:19.261 --> 00:52:22.445
...she's worth it.

733
00:52:23.932 --> 00:52:27.101
No. you...

734
00:52:27.102 --> 00:52:30.646
...go ahead and you get some rest.

735
00:52:30.647 --> 00:52:32.648
I'm tired too.

736
00:52:32.649 --> 00:52:36.443
I almost don't wanna click off here...

737
00:52:36.444 --> 00:52:39.405
...like maybe we won't get this back.

738
00:52:39.406 --> 00:52:43.966
- We will.
- Okay.

739
00:52:44.202 --> 00:52:47.637
I'll be here tomorrow.

740
00:52:48.248 --> 00:52:51.098
I know.

741
00:53:01.845 --> 00:53:05.279
I love you. son.

742
00:53:07.517 --> 00:53:10.451
I. uh...

743
00:53:11.229 --> 00:53:13.689
I love you too. Dad.

744
00:53:13.690 --> 00:53:16.415
And...

745
00:53:16.526 --> 00:53:20.253
...I've missed you so much.

746
00:53:20.906 --> 00:53:23.589
<font color=#ff00ff>[CLEARS THROAT]</font>

747
00:53:36.254 --> 00:53:38.672
<font color=#ff00ff>[LINE RINGS]</font>

748
00:53:38.673 --> 00:53:40.758
<font color=#FF551>JULIA:</font> <font color=#ff00ff>[ON RECORDING]</font> Hi.
this is Julia Sullivan.

749
00:53:40.759 --> 00:53:42.426
Please leave a message after the tone.

750
00:53:42.427 --> 00:53:45.304
<font color=#ff00ff>[ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS]</font>

751
00:53:45.305 --> 00:53:48.823
Hey. Ma. it's me. Uh...

752
00:53:50.352 --> 00:53:54.829
Just call me. We gotta talk.

753
00:54:07.494 --> 00:54:10.845
<font color=#ff00ff>[CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]</font>

754
00:54:20.799 --> 00:54:23.941
- Take over for me?
- All right.

755
00:54:24.594 --> 00:54:26.303
- Frank. what's going on?
<font color=#FF551>- FRANK:</font> Nothing.

756
00:54:26.304 --> 00:54:30.364
- I just wanted to see you. that's all.
- Yeah?

757
00:54:30.892 --> 00:54:33.018
I'm not going anywhere. Jules.

758
00:54:33.019 --> 00:54:35.271
Not for the rest of your life.

759
00:54:35.272 --> 00:54:38.232
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

760
00:54:38.233 --> 00:54:41.068
- I got a bad feeling today. I was worried.
- Huh?

761
00:54:41.069 --> 00:54:45.197
- Look at me. Not a scratch.
- Where's Johnny?

762
00:54:45.198 --> 00:54:47.408
He's at Gordo's. I tucked him in.

763
00:54:47.409 --> 00:54:48.909
You give him his drops?

764
00:54:48.910 --> 00:54:51.287
One in each ear.

765
00:54:51.288 --> 00:54:54.999
- What would you do without me?
- Probably marry some rich doctor.

766
00:54:55.000 --> 00:54:57.418
Never have to work.

767
00:54:57.419 --> 00:55:01.312
Oh. my God. What is he doing? Frank. I gotta...

768
00:55:01.881 --> 00:55:03.549
- Doctor. is that benazepril?
- Yes.

769
00:55:03.550 --> 00:55:06.719
I gave this patient 50 mils of
Benadryl. Mix them and he's dead.

770
00:55:06.720 --> 00:55:10.696
- Why wasn't I made aware of it?
- It's in his chart.

771
00:55:12.058 --> 00:55:13.892
<font color=#ff00ff>[MOUTHS]</font> I love you. Bye.

772
00:55:13.893 --> 00:55:16.994
<font color=#ff00ff>[MOUTHS]</font> I love you too.

773
00:55:52.640 --> 00:55:55.991
<font color=#ff00ff>[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]</font>

774
00:56:36.810 --> 00:56:40.161
<font color=#ff00ff>[JOHN PANTING]</font>

775
00:56:55.078 --> 00:56:57.678
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> Son?

776
00:57:03.962 --> 00:57:06.687
Come on.

777
00:57:09.008 --> 00:57:12.026
<font color=#ff00ff>[GASPING]</font>

778
00:57:27.026 --> 00:57:29.611
<font color=#ff00ff>[LINE RINGING]</font>

779
00:57:29.612 --> 00:57:31.905
- Hello. Ma?
<font color=#FF551>- WOMAN:</font> <i>Noah's Deli.</i>

780
00:57:31.906 --> 00:57:35.466
Oh. sorry.

781
00:57:40.999 --> 00:57:42.708
<font color=#ff00ff>[LINE RINGING]</font>

782
00:57:42.709 --> 00:57:46.378
<font color=#FF551>WOMAN:</font> <i>This is Noah's Deli.</i>

783
00:57:46.379 --> 00:57:49.730
<font color=#ff00ff>[LINE CLICKS AND DIAL TONE HUMS]</font>

784
00:58:02.187 --> 00:58:06.273
- Sam. I gotta talk to you.
- Excuse me?

785
00:58:06.274 --> 00:58:12.112
- Look. I'm sorry. but I gotta talk to you.
- How do you know my name?

786
00:58:12.113 --> 00:58:15.240
- Who are you?
- Who am I?

787
00:58:15.241 --> 00:58:17.743
Look. I don't know you.

788
00:58:17.744 --> 00:58:22.012
You don't know me? What do
you mean. you don't know me?

789
00:58:22.248 --> 00:58:25.918
Wait. I do know you. You're
Linda and Gordo's friend.

790
00:58:25.919 --> 00:58:27.711
The neighbor. The cop.

791
00:58:27.712 --> 00:58:30.938
What are you doing here?

792
00:58:31.674 --> 00:58:34.191
Um...

793
00:58:36.721 --> 00:58:38.972
I shouldn't have come here.

794
00:58:38.973 --> 00:58:44.410
I didn't... I didn't mean to upset you. I'm sorry.

795
00:58:48.775 --> 00:58:52.042
<font color=#FF551>SATCH:</font> Yeah. I'll take care of it.

796
00:59:17.637 --> 00:59:20.472
- What?
- Another rough night?

797
00:59:20.473 --> 00:59:23.976
- Is that it?
- Yeah. that's it.

798
00:59:23.977 --> 00:59:27.229
Do not disrespect me. John.

799
00:59:27.230 --> 00:59:34.001
Disrespect yourself all you want to. but
not me or anybody else here. Got that?

800
00:59:41.828 --> 00:59:44.496
We got the preliminary
forensics back on the skeleton.

801
00:59:44.497 --> 00:59:47.890
You wanna take a look at this.

802
00:59:54.966 --> 00:59:58.442
Bad memories.

803
00:59:58.761 --> 01:00:02.931
You imagine the odds of us
digging up a Nightingale murder?

804
01:00:02.932 --> 01:00:05.976
- She makes 10.
- Ten?

805
01:00:05.977 --> 01:00:07.978
No. I remember this case.

806
01:00:07.979 --> 01:00:11.497
It was three. He killed three women.

807
01:00:11.649 --> 01:00:15.960
What are you talking? You know
better than anybody. John.

808
01:00:19.073 --> 01:00:23.175
You looked at these files a thousand times.

809
01:00:32.837 --> 01:00:35.813
No.

810
01:01:00.114 --> 01:01:03.298
Dad. are you there?

811
01:01:03.451 --> 01:01:06.161
<font color=#ff00ff>[OVER RADIO]</font> <i>Can you hear me?</i>

812
01:01:06.162 --> 01:01:08.955
<i>Dad. I need you to be there.</i>

813
01:01:08.956 --> 01:01:11.500
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> Yeah. yeah. Chief.
I'm coming. I'm coming.

814
01:01:11.501 --> 01:01:15.394
Listen. there's something I need to t...

815
01:01:16.756 --> 01:01:19.606
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> Right here. Chief.

816
01:01:20.635 --> 01:01:23.387
- <i>Chief?</i>
- Something happened.

817
01:01:23.388 --> 01:01:26.932
- Something pretty bad.
- What's the matter. Johnny? What is it?

818
01:01:26.933 --> 01:01:31.520
- <i>Mom. Something happened to her in...</i>
- Your mom. What?

819
01:01:31.521 --> 01:01:33.271
She's not here.

820
01:01:33.272 --> 01:01:36.665
What do you mean. she's not there?

821
01:01:38.403 --> 01:01:43.198
She died. but it's like
it just happened. though.

822
01:01:43.199 --> 01:01:45.575
She died? Your mom just died?

823
01:01:45.576 --> 01:01:47.119
No. Dad.

824
01:01:47.120 --> 01:01:48.912
It happened a long time ago.

825
01:01:48.913 --> 01:01:51.581
A long time ago for me.

826
01:01:51.582 --> 01:01:53.083
When?

827
01:01:53.084 --> 01:01:58.630
October 22nd. 1969.

828
01:01:58.631 --> 01:02:01.633
That's now. Johnny. That's next week.

829
01:02:01.634 --> 01:02:05.637
How...? You gotta tell me how.

830
01:02:05.638 --> 01:02:08.432
- She was murdered.
- Murdered? What are you talking about?

831
01:02:08.433 --> 01:02:12.227
Listen to me. There was this case.
a serial. They never caught him.

832
01:02:12.228 --> 01:02:16.690
But he murdered three women.
all nurses. between '68 and '69.

833
01:02:16.691 --> 01:02:18.275
They call him the Nightingale.

834
01:02:18.276 --> 01:02:20.694
Nightingale? We've been
watching that on the news.

835
01:02:20.695 --> 01:02:24.072
- I was worried about your mother. She said...
- Dad. we did something.

836
01:02:24.073 --> 01:02:26.408
Something to make it worse.

837
01:02:26.409 --> 01:02:30.162
- I don't understand.
- He didn't just kill three women anymore.

838
01:02:30.163 --> 01:02:33.331
He's killed 10. Something
we did changed the past.

839
01:02:33.332 --> 01:02:35.542
- But how come your mother...?
- Think about it.

840
01:02:35.543 --> 01:02:40.046
Everything you did is different than if
you'd never gotten out of that warehouse.

841
01:02:40.047 --> 01:02:42.424
Now. what did you do last night. Dad?

842
01:02:42.425 --> 01:02:47.304
I talked to you. I put you on the bike...

843
01:02:47.305 --> 01:02:51.349
...I tucked you in at Gordo's and I went
to see your mother over at the hospital.

844
01:02:51.350 --> 01:02:52.851
Oh. shit.

845
01:02:52.852 --> 01:02:55.437
That's it. She wasn't supposed to be there.

846
01:02:55.438 --> 01:02:58.607
Butch got her. It was the night
of the fire. He brought her home.

847
01:02:58.608 --> 01:03:01.485
- Something happened at the hospital?
- That's the beginning.

848
01:03:01.486 --> 01:03:05.447
It could've been anywhere. place. time
that she wouldn't have been if you'd died.

849
01:03:05.448 --> 01:03:08.366
I'll take her away from here.
I have to take her away from...

850
01:03:08.367 --> 01:03:11.912
- He cannot hurt her if I take her away.
- What about the others?

851
01:03:11.913 --> 01:03:14.080
<i>What about the others. Dad?</i>

852
01:03:14.081 --> 01:03:17.167
- I'll warn them.
- It'll never work. They'll think you're crazy.

853
01:03:17.168 --> 01:03:20.629
But I gotta do something. You don't
even know what this guy looks like.

854
01:03:20.630 --> 01:03:24.216
- You don't know who he is.
- No. because nobody got any...

855
01:03:24.217 --> 01:03:27.776
Hold on. Wait a minute.

856
01:03:28.387 --> 01:03:30.430
Dad. I may not know who he is...

857
01:03:30.431 --> 01:03:34.226
...but I know where he's gonna be and
what he's gonna do before he gets there.

858
01:03:34.227 --> 01:03:37.562
What do I do? Call the police?
They're not gonna believe me.

859
01:03:37.563 --> 01:03:40.732
They will if they catch him in
the act. You can make that happen.

860
01:03:40.733 --> 01:03:42.192
No. Johnny. I don't know.

861
01:03:42.193 --> 01:03:46.112
- I don't know. I'm a firefighter. not a cop.
- I'm a cop. This is what I do.

862
01:03:46.113 --> 01:03:48.740
This is something we have to do.

863
01:03:48.741 --> 01:03:50.075
If the ham stops working?

864
01:03:50.076 --> 01:03:52.494
- If I can't reach you?
- Get Mom the hell out.

865
01:03:52.495 --> 01:03:56.373
<i>But. Dad. those other women
were not supposed to die.</i>

866
01:03:56.374 --> 01:03:58.575
If we don't do something
to try to stop this guy...

867
01:03:58.576 --> 01:04:03.129
...we're gonna have to live with
that for the rest of our lives.

868
01:04:03.130 --> 01:04:04.923
Okay.

869
01:04:04.924 --> 01:04:08.051
- Okay. tell me what to do.
- <i>All right.</i>

870
01:04:08.052 --> 01:04:11.054
The next victim is Carrie
Reynolds. It happens tomorrow.

871
01:04:11.055 --> 01:04:14.349
Case file says she left the
Roosevelt Hospital at 6...

872
01:04:14.350 --> 01:04:16.560
...showed up at Cozy's Bar around 6:30...

873
01:04:16.561 --> 01:04:19.479
<i>...she walked out of that bar around 7:30...</i>

874
01:04:19.480 --> 01:04:23.608
<i>...and they found her dead in
an alley behind the bar at 8:00.</i>

875
01:04:23.609 --> 01:04:27.445
<i>I want you to follow her. see if anybody's
watching her or hitting on her...</i>

876
01:04:27.446 --> 01:04:30.282
<i>...because I'm betting when
she walks out of that place...</i>

877
01:04:30.283 --> 01:04:32.284
<i>...somebody's gonna come out with her.</i>

878
01:04:32.285 --> 01:04:34.995
<i>When they do. you call the cops.</i>

879
01:04:34.996 --> 01:04:37.714
<font color=#FF551>- MAN:</font> Hi. Carrie.
- Hi. Glen. How you doing?

880
01:04:37.715 --> 01:04:40.125
<font color=#FF551>GLEN:</font> <i>Really good.</i>

881
01:04:40.126 --> 01:04:41.835
<font color=#FF551>CARRIE:</font> <i>Thanks for ordering.</i>

882
01:04:41.836 --> 01:04:44.880
<font color=#FF551>NIXON:</font> <font color=#ff00ff>[ON TV]</font> <i>The American people want peace.</i>

883
01:04:44.881 --> 01:04:47.173
<i>We believe in peace.</i>

884
01:04:47.174 --> 01:04:52.637
<i>We have fought our wars in this century
because we wanted peace.</i>

885
01:04:52.638 --> 01:04:55.891
<i>And we want to bring the
war in Vietnam to an end...</i>

886
01:04:55.892 --> 01:05:02.287
<i>in a way that will promote not a
temporary but a lasting peace.</i>

887
01:05:16.329 --> 01:05:19.247
<font color=#FF551>DELANEY:</font> <i>busiest intersection during
tomorrow evening's rush hour.</i>

888
01:05:19.248 --> 01:05:24.419
<font color=#FF551>- BARTENDER:</font> <i>Two JBs on the rocks.</i>
<font color=#FF551>- DELANEY:</font> <i>Steve Delaney. NBC News.</i>

889
01:05:24.420 --> 01:05:26.504
<font color=#FF551>BARTENDER:</font> <i>Yeah.</i>

890
01:05:26.505 --> 01:05:28.173
From the girls. pal. Cool.

891
01:05:28.174 --> 01:05:31.468
<font color=#FF551>ANCHOR:</font> <i>In Chicago. students from
Mundelein College. the capital school...</i>

892
01:05:31.469 --> 01:05:35.347
<i>...have been passing out leaflets
in supermarkets to get support.</i>

893
01:05:35.348 --> 01:05:38.600
<font color=#FF551>- MAN:</font> <i>We're gonna have an evening vigil...</i>
- Thanks.

894
01:05:38.601 --> 01:05:41.853
<font color=#FF551>ANCHOR:</font> <i>At Northwestern University Law
School. which held a rally today...</i>

895
01:05:41.854 --> 01:05:46.691
<i>...60 percent of the students felt that
the U.S. should get out of the war.</i>

896
01:05:46.692 --> 01:05:49.194
<font color=#FF551>- FRANK:</font> I was...
- Sit down.

897
01:05:49.195 --> 01:05:50.946
<font color=#FF551>- FRANK:</font> Yeah.
- Fireman. huh?

898
01:05:50.947 --> 01:05:54.324
<font color=#FF551>- FRANK:</font> Yeah. I'm not really...
- A married fireman.

899
01:05:54.325 --> 01:05:56.284
- Yeah.
<font color=#FF551>- WOMAN1:</font> Oh. what the hell.

900
01:05:56.285 --> 01:06:00.538
- What do they call you?
- Uh. Frank.

901
01:06:00.539 --> 01:06:03.890
<font color=#ff00ff>[TELEPHONE RINGING]</font>

902
01:06:05.211 --> 01:06:07.545
Seven-four Homicide.

903
01:06:07.546 --> 01:06:10.090
Yeah. it's me.

904
01:06:10.091 --> 01:06:13.066
You're kidding.

905
01:06:13.719 --> 01:06:15.387
Hold on.

906
01:06:15.388 --> 01:06:16.972
Spell that for me.

907
01:06:16.973 --> 01:06:21.241
Okay. okay. Thanks. Mario.

908
01:06:22.520 --> 01:06:24.145
Our lucky break.

909
01:06:24.146 --> 01:06:27.482
Mario ID'd the dental. Her name is Mary Finelli.

910
01:06:27.483 --> 01:06:30.777
Reported missing April 16th. 1968.

911
01:06:30.778 --> 01:06:33.196
April 16th?

912
01:06:33.197 --> 01:06:37.534
- That means she was the first.
- Which means he probably knew her.

913
01:06:37.535 --> 01:06:40.552
This case just got hot.

914
01:06:41.789 --> 01:06:43.832
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> She's gone.

915
01:06:43.833 --> 01:06:46.600
Carrie Reynolds isn't in here.

916
01:06:47.878 --> 01:06:50.562
Who?

917
01:06:51.882 --> 01:06:54.691
He did it.

918
01:06:57.930 --> 01:07:01.099
<font color=#ff00ff>[OVER RADIO]</font> <i>Carrie Reynolds
is alive and well. Dad.</i>

919
01:07:01.100 --> 01:07:02.434
I'll be damned.

920
01:07:02.435 --> 01:07:03.985
- Did you see him?
- No.

921
01:07:03.986 --> 01:07:06.813
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> <i>Figure who he is?</i>
- No. I messed up.

922
01:07:06.814 --> 01:07:09.607
<i>I kept talking. I was afraid
to let her out of my sight.</i>

923
01:07:09.608 --> 01:07:11.609
<i>Whoever it was. he must have backed off.</i>

924
01:07:11.610 --> 01:07:14.946
<i>That's okay. We're gonna
get him. This is gonna work.</i>

925
01:07:14.947 --> 01:07:19.242
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> <i>I hope so. So tell me. what else you got?</i>

926
01:07:19.243 --> 01:07:23.079
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> <i>We caught a break. Found his first victim.</i>

927
01:07:23.080 --> 01:07:25.498
- <i>Her name is Mary Finelli.</i>
<font color=#FF551>- GORDO:</font> Thanks. Mrs. Sullivan.

928
01:07:25.499 --> 01:07:27.208
Yeah. hang on a sec. John.

929
01:07:27.209 --> 01:07:31.713
Hey. Jules. there's somebody
I want you to talk to. okay?

930
01:07:31.714 --> 01:07:34.174
Remember I told you about this guy. John?

931
01:07:34.175 --> 01:07:36.426
<i>I want you to say hello to him.</i>

932
01:07:36.427 --> 01:07:37.844
- <i>John.</i>
- Yeah.

933
01:07:37.845 --> 01:07:42.114
<i>Say hello to my wife. Julia.</i>

934
01:07:42.808 --> 01:07:46.019
- Hi.
<font color=#FF551>- JULIA:</font> <i>Hi. John.</i>

935
01:07:46.020 --> 01:07:48.396
<i>Frank tells me you're a cop.</i>

936
01:07:48.397 --> 01:07:50.065
Yeah. that's right.

937
01:07:50.066 --> 01:07:54.319
Yeah? Well. my 6-year-old keeps telling
us he wants to be a policeman...

938
01:07:54.320 --> 01:07:57.072
...right after he retires from the majors.

939
01:07:57.073 --> 01:07:59.949
We just bought him a badge and
a whistle for his birthday.

940
01:07:59.950 --> 01:08:03.703
Yeah. I remember. I used to play cops
and robbers all the time. but you...

941
01:08:03.704 --> 01:08:06.831
My mom wouldn't let me have a toy gun.

942
01:08:06.832 --> 01:08:10.001
Sounds like your mom and I would get along.

943
01:08:10.002 --> 01:08:13.755
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> <i>Yeah. she's pretty
special. I'm real proud of her.</i>

944
01:08:13.756 --> 01:08:18.051
<font color=#FF551>JULIA:</font> <i>Well. I bet she's proud of
you too. huh. being a cop and all?</i>

945
01:08:18.052 --> 01:08:19.636
I hope so.

946
01:08:19.637 --> 01:08:23.098
I hope... hope she knows how much I love her.

947
01:08:23.099 --> 01:08:24.849
<font color=#FF551>JULIA:</font> <i>Oh. she knows.</i>

948
01:08:24.850 --> 01:08:27.602
<i>Moms always know how much
their kids love them.</i>

949
01:08:27.603 --> 01:08:31.913
Even if they don't tell them
all the time like they should.

950
01:08:33.275 --> 01:08:37.153
<i>Well. I gotta go. It was
good talking to you. John.</i>

951
01:08:37.154 --> 01:08:38.363
Yeah. you... you too.

952
01:08:38.364 --> 01:08:41.366
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> <i>I wanna talk on Daddy's radio.</i>
<font color=#FF551>- FRANK:</font> <i>Okay. Chief. go ahead.</i>

953
01:08:41.367 --> 01:08:45.886
<font color=#FF551>- JULIA:</font> Okay. Say good night to John.
- Good night. John.

954
01:08:47.289 --> 01:08:50.515
Good night. there. Chief.

955
01:08:50.835 --> 01:08:52.961
<font color=#FF551>JULIA:</font> Okay. guys. bedtime.

956
01:08:52.962 --> 01:08:55.171
No. I wanna talk on the radio too.

957
01:08:55.172 --> 01:08:59.384
<font color=#FF551>- FRANK:</font> All right. Gordo. Come here.
<font color=#FF551>- JULIA:</font> <i>Okay. two minutes. then bedtime.</i>

958
01:08:59.385 --> 01:09:00.802
- I'm off to bed.
<font color=#FF551>- FRANK:</font> Sit there.

959
01:09:00.803 --> 01:09:02.387
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> One more cookie.
<font color=#FF551>- JULIA:</font> <i>No.</i>

960
01:09:02.388 --> 01:09:04.222
- <i>No more cookies.</i>
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> Just one more.

961
01:09:04.223 --> 01:09:06.224
<font color=#FF551>GORDO:</font> <i>This is the space cowboy.</i>

962
01:09:06.225 --> 01:09:10.395
I'm an intergalactic traveler
from the federation planet Earth.

963
01:09:10.396 --> 01:09:14.232
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> <i>Gordo?</i>
- How do you know my name. mister?

964
01:09:14.233 --> 01:09:19.320
<font color=#FF551>- FRANK:</font> <i>Come on. Elvis. let's go outside.</i>
- Hey. listen. Gordo. Uh...

965
01:09:19.321 --> 01:09:21.239
My name is Santa Claus.

966
01:09:21.240 --> 01:09:26.202
And I'm going to give you the biggest
Christmas present that you ever had.

967
01:09:26.203 --> 01:09:28.413
I better give you my address. then.

968
01:09:28.414 --> 01:09:31.708
No. no. no. don't worry about
it. kid. Now. this is important.

969
01:09:31.709 --> 01:09:34.794
Something you gotta remember for a long time.

970
01:09:34.795 --> 01:09:36.713
Yahoo.

971
01:09:36.714 --> 01:09:37.922
What's that?

972
01:09:37.923 --> 01:09:40.967
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> <i>Well. it's a magic word. It's like...</i>

973
01:09:40.968 --> 01:09:43.344
<i>Like abracadabra. but even better.</i>

974
01:09:43.345 --> 01:09:46.806
<i>Try it out. kid. Yahoo.</i>

975
01:09:46.807 --> 01:09:49.517
- Yahoo.
- <i>You got it. space cowboy.</i>

976
01:09:49.518 --> 01:09:51.936
Okay. Gordo. Your two minutes are up.

977
01:09:51.937 --> 01:09:55.231
- Now go upstairs and write it down.
<font color=#FF551>- GORDO:</font> <i>Okay. mister.</i>

978
01:09:55.232 --> 01:09:57.525
- I mean. Santa.
<font color=#FF551>- FRANK:</font> <i>Come on.</i>

979
01:09:57.526 --> 01:10:00.570
<i>Let's go. Stay there. John. I'll be right back.</i>

980
01:10:00.571 --> 01:10:04.449
<i>All right. come on. upstairs. There you
go. Jules. got a live one down here.</i>

981
01:10:04.450 --> 01:10:07.133
<i> Coming your way.</i>

982
01:10:07.453 --> 01:10:08.995
<i>Yeah. Chief.</i>

983
01:10:08.996 --> 01:10:11.856
- Are you still there?
- Yeah. What do we do now?

984
01:10:11.857 --> 01:10:14.292
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> <i>Okay. Sissy Clark.</i>

985
01:10:14.293 --> 01:10:17.378
- <i>423 Greenwich Street...</i>
- Okay. hang on. hang on.

986
01:10:17.379 --> 01:10:19.255
- Go ahead.
- Sissy Clark.

987
01:10:19.256 --> 01:10:23.343
423 Greenwich Street. Apartment 2E. tomorrow.

988
01:10:23.344 --> 01:10:25.645
- Okay. 2E. All right.
- <i>Nurse.</i>

989
01:10:25.646 --> 01:10:31.017
Moonlights as a cocktail waitress
at the Kaleidoscope on West 63rd.

990
01:10:31.018 --> 01:10:33.645
Left work at 2 a.m.

991
01:10:33.646 --> 01:10:38.483
Was killed in her apartment between 2:15 and 5.

992
01:10:38.484 --> 01:10:39.984
Okay. I got it.

993
01:10:39.985 --> 01:10:43.655
<i>Now. Dad. I don't know how long
this thing is gonna keep working.</i>

994
01:10:43.656 --> 01:10:46.032
<i>Hope we'll be able to talk again.</i>

995
01:10:46.033 --> 01:10:48.842
<i>Just be careful. all right?</i>

996
01:11:23.195 --> 01:11:26.531
<font color=#FF551>WOMAN:</font> <i>I'm happy you found her. detective.</i>

997
01:11:26.532 --> 01:11:31.411
It makes it easier now to know for sure.

998
01:11:31.412 --> 01:11:34.179
You know?

999
01:11:35.416 --> 01:11:38.509
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> Can I keep these
for a while. Mrs. Finelli?

1000
01:11:38.510 --> 01:11:40.378
<font color=#ff00ff>[SIGHS]</font>

1001
01:11:40.379 --> 01:11:43.548
Okay. just let me walk you through it.

1002
01:11:43.549 --> 01:11:46.884
<font color=#FF551>SATCH:</font> <i>I'm all ears.</i>

1003
01:11:46.885 --> 01:11:50.904
Three guys show up in both
the yearbook and diary.

1004
01:11:51.557 --> 01:11:55.435
First guy passed away 10 years ago.

1005
01:11:55.436 --> 01:11:58.521
Second guy died in Vietnam.

1006
01:11:58.522 --> 01:12:01.566
And the third one is Daryl Simpson.

1007
01:12:01.567 --> 01:12:05.236
So I ran him though BCI. Got a hit.

1008
01:12:05.237 --> 01:12:09.073
Busted for sexual assault eight days
after the last Nightingale murder.

1009
01:12:09.074 --> 01:12:11.743
March 22nd. 1970.

1010
01:12:11.744 --> 01:12:14.912
<font color=#FF551>SATCH:</font> So you think the murders stopped
because he was off the street...

1011
01:12:14.913 --> 01:12:16.789
...and by the time he got paroled...

1012
01:12:16.790 --> 01:12:19.417
...he had smartened up
enough to control himself?

1013
01:12:19.418 --> 01:12:21.753
It's not the first time that's been true.

1014
01:12:21.754 --> 01:12:27.023
I'm telling you. I got a feeling
about this guy. This is him. Satch.

1015
01:12:30.304 --> 01:12:33.655
<font color=#ff00ff>[STEPPENWOLF'S "SOOKIE.
SOOKIE" PLAYING ON STEREO]</font>

1016
01:12:36.435 --> 01:12:38.269
- Can I get you another?
- Yeah. another one.

1017
01:12:38.270 --> 01:12:42.607
<i># Let it hang out. baby #</i>

1018
01:12:42.608 --> 01:12:46.793
<i># Let it hang out now #</i>

1019
01:12:47.446 --> 01:12:48.946
Can I get you another one?

1020
01:12:48.947 --> 01:12:51.115
- No. thanks. I'm good.
- Okay.

1021
01:12:51.116 --> 01:12:54.243
<i># Everybody work out #</i>

1022
01:12:54.244 --> 01:12:55.870
Anything else. sir?

1023
01:12:55.871 --> 01:12:59.207
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> Sexual assault. Daryl. Five years.

1024
01:12:59.208 --> 01:13:01.459
But you got lucky. right?

1025
01:13:01.460 --> 01:13:03.711
You got away with something else.

1026
01:13:03.712 --> 01:13:05.963
Something you figured nobody knows about.

1027
01:13:05.964 --> 01:13:09.584
- What I know is what I told you.
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> Let me tell you what I know. Daryl.

1028
01:13:09.585 --> 01:13:12.637
You went to St. Ambrose with Mary.
You lived five blocks from her.

1029
01:13:12.638 --> 01:13:14.764
You liked her. but she ain't interested.

1030
01:13:14.765 --> 01:13:17.392
- <i>So that must have hurt. huh?</i>
- So what?

1031
01:13:17.393 --> 01:13:21.244
- <i>So. what did you do about it. Daryl?</i>
- Nothing.

1032
01:13:28.612 --> 01:13:30.571
<font color=#FF551>MAN:</font> Spare a smoke?

1033
01:13:30.572 --> 01:13:35.592
Yeah. Here. I'm trying to quit.

1034
01:13:38.539 --> 01:13:40.540
Oh. my God.

1035
01:13:40.541 --> 01:13:42.166
What is this?

1036
01:13:42.167 --> 01:13:45.628
Oh. Jesus. Jesus. Get that away from me!

1037
01:13:45.629 --> 01:13:50.800
Sandra Moore. Patty Ryan. Mary Finelli.
These names mean anything to you. pal?

1038
01:13:50.801 --> 01:13:52.969
Julia Sullivan. Does she mean anything?

1039
01:13:52.970 --> 01:13:56.863
Well. she means something to me!

1040
01:14:07.568 --> 01:14:10.903
See you. fireman. Don't talk so much next time.

1041
01:14:10.904 --> 01:14:13.114
Gus. will you run my tips while I go change?

1042
01:14:13.115 --> 01:14:15.840
- Sure. Sissy.
- Thanks.

1043
01:14:32.759 --> 01:14:35.178
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> <font color=#ff00ff>[ON MONITOR]</font> <i>You know. Daryl...</i>

1044
01:14:35.179 --> 01:14:39.531
<i>...sometimes despite all the training
that we cops go through...</i>

1045
01:14:39.892 --> 01:14:44.020
...despite all that we are taught
about right and wrong...

1046
01:14:44.021 --> 01:14:47.815
...despite all that we would
like to honor in ourselves...

1047
01:14:47.816 --> 01:14:51.084
...we can come to a place...

1048
01:14:51.111 --> 01:14:53.905
<i>...where we don't give a damn.</i>

1049
01:14:53.906 --> 01:14:56.699
<i>Know what I mean?</i>

1050
01:14:56.700 --> 01:15:00.077
You're going to tell me everything
I need to know now.

1051
01:15:00.078 --> 01:15:03.581
John. you got a minute?

1052
01:15:03.582 --> 01:15:07.267
Yeah. sure.

1053
01:15:13.509 --> 01:15:15.218
He ain't the guy. John.

1054
01:15:15.219 --> 01:15:18.337
He didn't look at the photos.
Doesn't mean he isn't the one.

1055
01:15:18.338 --> 01:15:19.722
Not everyone fits the profile.

1056
01:15:19.723 --> 01:15:24.617
If he was gonna give up something.
he would've done it already.

1057
01:15:33.445 --> 01:15:35.696
<font color=#ff00ff>[SHOUTING]</font>

1058
01:15:35.697 --> 01:15:40.925
You following me? You following me?

1059
01:15:41.787 --> 01:15:45.164
I asked you a question. asshole.

1060
01:15:45.165 --> 01:15:47.708
Mary Finelli.

1061
01:15:47.709 --> 01:15:50.768
<font color=#ff00ff>[GRUNTING AND SHOUTING]</font>

1062
01:16:13.485 --> 01:16:16.320
<font color=#ff00ff>[DOOR OPENS]</font>

1063
01:16:16.321 --> 01:16:20.783
- Whoa. Dude. what happened to him?
<font color=#FF551>- MAN:</font> It was a bad trip. man.

1064
01:16:20.784 --> 01:16:23.661
Little time kissing the porcelain.
he'll be fine. You know?

1065
01:16:23.662 --> 01:16:27.639
- Yeah. I understand that.
<font color=#FF551>- MAN:</font> All right. Come on. pal.

1066
01:17:17.883 --> 01:17:20.551
Open up. Ms. Clark. open the door!

1067
01:17:20.552 --> 01:17:24.805
Open the door! It's the police! Open the door!

1068
01:17:24.806 --> 01:17:28.517
It's okay. ma'am. Go back inside.
It's the police. Are you in there?

1069
01:17:28.518 --> 01:17:31.869
Open up. I know you're in there!

1070
01:17:32.814 --> 01:17:37.542
Sissy Clark. Open the door. Open the door.

1071
01:17:42.240 --> 01:17:44.450
<font color=#ff00ff>[THE HONEYDRIPPERS' "SEA OF LOVE"
LOOPING ON RECORD PLAYER]</font>

1072
01:17:44.451 --> 01:17:54.015
<i> # Do you remember when we...?
Do you remember when we...? #</i>

1073
01:18:24.449 --> 01:18:27.118
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> <i>He killed her.</i>

1074
01:18:27.119 --> 01:18:31.038
- And I couldn't do a damn thing to stop it.
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> <i>Dad. I said it's not your fault.</i>

1075
01:18:31.039 --> 01:18:32.540
Yes. it is.

1076
01:18:32.541 --> 01:18:34.959
<i>We changed everything. Johnny. eh?</i>

1077
01:18:34.960 --> 01:18:38.746
- It's like we cheated.
- <i>All right. Dad. we can't go back...</i>

1078
01:18:38.747 --> 01:18:40.548
...because you didn't die in that fire.

1079
01:18:40.549 --> 01:18:43.217
And no matter what you do.
nothing is gonna change it.

1080
01:18:43.218 --> 01:18:46.554
So all we can do is deal with
this and try to make it right.

1081
01:18:46.555 --> 01:18:50.349
- I'm not a cop. I'm not fooling anybody.
- I know. I know. but we can.

1082
01:18:50.350 --> 01:18:54.994
We can do it together. Remember spirit and guts?

1083
01:18:56.022 --> 01:18:58.649
John. he's got my driver's license.

1084
01:18:58.650 --> 01:19:01.277
- What?
- He took my driver's license.

1085
01:19:01.278 --> 01:19:02.987
He knows where we live.

1086
01:19:02.988 --> 01:19:05.656
He took your dri...? He took your wallet?

1087
01:19:05.657 --> 01:19:08.617
<i>Yeah. well. he tossed the wallet.
but he kept the license.</i>

1088
01:19:08.618 --> 01:19:10.786
- Where's your wallet?
- It's in my pocket.

1089
01:19:10.787 --> 01:19:13.497
- <i>Oh. God. We got him. Dad. You got him.</i>
- What?

1090
01:19:13.498 --> 01:19:15.916
His prints. You got his prints.

1091
01:19:15.917 --> 01:19:20.154
- Listen. you gotta get me that wallet.
- How the hell am I supposed to do that?

1092
01:19:20.155 --> 01:19:23.031
<i>As carefully as possible. Take your wallet out.</i>

1093
01:19:23.032 --> 01:19:24.842
- <i>But just touch it on the corners.</i>
- What?

1094
01:19:24.843 --> 01:19:27.011
- Please. Dad. just do it.
- Okay. all right.

1095
01:19:27.012 --> 01:19:29.138
- All right. all right.
- All right.

1096
01:19:29.139 --> 01:19:33.092
- Okay. all right. I got it.
- All right. now listen.

1097
01:19:33.093 --> 01:19:35.352
I want you to wrap it up.

1098
01:19:35.353 --> 01:19:38.681
Put it in one of the plastic bags
you keep extra transistors in.

1099
01:19:38.682 --> 01:19:41.684
- Yeah. I see where you're going. Chief.
- <i>Beautiful. Okay.</i>

1100
01:19:41.685 --> 01:19:43.444
Now I want you to hide it somewhere.

1101
01:19:43.445 --> 01:19:48.032
<i>Somewhere where nobody's gonna
find it for the next 30 years.</i>

1102
01:19:48.033 --> 01:19:50.618
- <i>I think maybe. uh...</i>
- Where?

1103
01:19:50.619 --> 01:19:52.611
The. uh. window seat in the dining room.

1104
01:19:52.612 --> 01:19:55.831
There's a loose board on
the left. on the bottom.

1105
01:19:55.832 --> 01:19:58.266
Perfect. Beautiful.

1106
01:20:14.309 --> 01:20:18.744
- It's in.
- Great. Okay. I'm after it.

1107
01:20:29.157 --> 01:20:33.726
We're in business! Now just
sit tight and don't worry!

1108
01:20:34.955 --> 01:20:37.597
Wow.

1109
01:21:04.901 --> 01:21:07.444
And the winner is...

1110
01:21:07.445 --> 01:21:10.406
<i>Oh. man. It's a cop.</i>

1111
01:21:10.407 --> 01:21:13.132
What the hell?

1112
01:21:20.458 --> 01:21:24.018
Son of a bitch.

1113
01:21:36.725 --> 01:21:39.935
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> Hey. Mr. Shepard. How are you?

1114
01:21:39.936 --> 01:21:42.313
<font color=#FF551>SHEPARD:</font> Who's that? Oh. hi. detective.

1115
01:21:42.314 --> 01:21:46.108
Just came by to wrap things up
over there. Thought I'd say hello.

1116
01:21:46.109 --> 01:21:48.352
Glad you did. Glad you did.

1117
01:21:48.353 --> 01:21:51.754
- Come on in.
- Thank you.

1118
01:21:54.442 --> 01:21:57.194
- Buy you a cup of coffee?
- Sure.

1119
01:21:57.195 --> 01:22:00.939
- Black? Sugar? Milk?
- Oh. you know. It's all good.

1120
01:22:00.940 --> 01:22:04.091
<i>You'll get black.</i>

1121
01:22:07.997 --> 01:22:10.833
Fresh pot.

1122
01:22:10.834 --> 01:22:13.710
- You know Jack?
- Not really.

1123
01:22:13.711 --> 01:22:15.087
He's still on the job?

1124
01:22:15.088 --> 01:22:19.899
Well. he does a little PI work now
and then. but he's mostly retired.

1125
01:22:20.051 --> 01:22:23.554
Living off his pension. huh?

1126
01:22:23.555 --> 01:22:27.683
Jack got caught up in them Knapp hearings.

1127
01:22:27.684 --> 01:22:31.353
Set up by some dirty cops who needed a fall guy.

1128
01:22:31.354 --> 01:22:34.022
Hurt him bad. Would have
broke his mother's heart.

1129
01:22:34.023 --> 01:22:36.441
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> Is she around?
- Who?

1130
01:22:36.442 --> 01:22:41.921
- Your wife.
- Oh. no. She passed on a long time ago.

1131
01:22:43.199 --> 01:22:46.592
Long time ago.

1132
01:22:51.457 --> 01:22:52.875
I'm sorry.

1133
01:22:52.876 --> 01:22:56.060
Well. that's okay.

1134
01:23:01.426 --> 01:23:04.443
Can I ask how she died?

1135
01:23:08.933 --> 01:23:12.284
Well. she...

1136
01:23:13.354 --> 01:23:15.939
She was murdered. detective.

1137
01:23:15.940 --> 01:23:19.276
<i>An ugly one. to tell you the truth.</i>

1138
01:23:19.277 --> 01:23:23.629
<i>Mother of a cop. and they never
found the bastard who did it.</i>

1139
01:23:35.585 --> 01:23:38.143
- Hey.
- <i>Hey.</i>

1140
01:23:39.305 --> 01:23:43.282
<font color=#FF551>- MAN:</font> <i>All right. I'll have another.
<font color=#FF551>- BARTENDER:</font> <i>All right.</i></i>

1141
01:23:57.782 --> 01:24:00.299
You on the job?

1142
01:24:03.288 --> 01:24:06.331
A long time ago.

1143
01:24:06.332 --> 01:24:08.292
- Do I know you?
- I look familiar?

1144
01:24:08.293 --> 01:24:09.793
No.

1145
01:24:09.794 --> 01:24:13.338
- What house you work?
- The 7-4 Homicide.

1146
01:24:13.339 --> 01:24:17.009
- A hotshot.
- No. just working the job.

1147
01:24:17.010 --> 01:24:18.469
Yeah. I hear that. pal.

1148
01:24:18.470 --> 01:24:22.973
As a matter of fact. I caught a
case that goes back to your day.

1149
01:24:22.974 --> 01:24:26.033
One of the Nightingale murders.

1150
01:24:26.186 --> 01:24:28.854
- No kidding?
- No. Missing teenager.

1151
01:24:28.855 --> 01:24:33.067
Disappeared back in '68. They
found her bones last week.

1152
01:24:33.068 --> 01:24:36.320
Buried behind some old
diner out by Dyckman Street.

1153
01:24:36.321 --> 01:24:38.572
Mary Finelli.

1154
01:24:38.573 --> 01:24:42.326
Talk about dumb luck. The odds of anybody
finding that girl 30 years later...

1155
01:24:42.327 --> 01:24:46.121
...and the chances of hitting
a dental. heh. forget about it.

1156
01:24:46.122 --> 01:24:48.916
The best part is. she's the first victim.

1157
01:24:48.917 --> 01:24:51.510
And she knew the killer...

1158
01:24:51.511 --> 01:24:56.272
...so I'm betting those old bones
are gonna do a lot of talking.

1159
01:24:59.010 --> 01:25:03.055
Not for nothing. The past is a funny
thing. We all have skeletons in the closet.

1160
01:25:03.056 --> 01:25:06.517
You just never know when they're
gonna pop up and bite you in the ass.

1161
01:25:06.518 --> 01:25:09.535
Huh. Jack?

1162
01:25:12.357 --> 01:25:14.358
You changed your MO.

1163
01:25:14.359 --> 01:25:18.946
If they knew your mother was a Nightingale.
they would have looked at the family.

1164
01:25:18.947 --> 01:25:22.298
They would've looked at you.

1165
01:25:26.704 --> 01:25:28.539
What are you looking at?

1166
01:25:28.540 --> 01:25:31.375
Stealing your life away.

1167
01:25:31.376 --> 01:25:34.086
You went down 30 years ago. pal.

1168
01:25:34.087 --> 01:25:37.521
You just don't know it yet.

1169
01:25:57.902 --> 01:26:01.086
<font color=#ff00ff>[BAND PLAYING "STAR SPANGLED BANNER" ON TV]</font>

1170
01:26:02.574 --> 01:26:03.907
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> A cop?

1171
01:26:03.908 --> 01:26:07.536
He's a cop? What the hell am
I supposed to do with that?

1172
01:26:07.537 --> 01:26:08.912
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> Call the FBI. Use a pay phone.

1173
01:26:08.913 --> 01:26:10.080
<font color=#ff00ff>[DOORBELL RINGS]</font>

1174
01:26:10.081 --> 01:26:12.666
Don't give them your name. Tell
them Shepard killed Finelli...

1175
01:26:12.667 --> 01:26:15.878
- ...Clark and the others. He's the Nightingale.
<font color=#FF551>- JULIA:</font> I'll get it.

1176
01:26:15.879 --> 01:26:18.630
Then tell them where Finelli's body is buried.

1177
01:26:18.631 --> 01:26:20.716
- They can connect him to her.
- Right here?

1178
01:26:20.717 --> 01:26:23.427
- They search his place. they find souvenirs.
<font color=#FF551>- JULIA:</font> Yes.

1179
01:26:23.428 --> 01:26:26.263
He always took a piece of
jewelry from his victims.

1180
01:26:26.264 --> 01:26:29.240
<font color=#FF551>SATCH:</font> Hey. Frank.

1181
01:26:30.935 --> 01:26:33.478
What are you doing here? Are you off today?

1182
01:26:33.479 --> 01:26:35.397
- We need to have a conversation.
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> Dad?

1183
01:26:35.398 --> 01:26:37.357
Hang on a sec. John.

1184
01:26:37.358 --> 01:26:40.277
Uh. I'm kind of in the middle
of something important.

1185
01:26:40.278 --> 01:26:42.446
- Mind if we do this...?
- I'm sorry. Frank...

1186
01:26:42.447 --> 01:26:46.074
...but we need to step outside right now and...

1187
01:26:46.075 --> 01:26:48.118
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> Dad. talk to me. What's going on?

1188
01:26:48.119 --> 01:26:51.413
Uh. John. Satch is here and he's...

1189
01:26:51.414 --> 01:26:54.416
- He's with his partner.
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> What the hell's going on?

1190
01:26:54.417 --> 01:26:56.168
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> Just hang on a sec.

1191
01:26:56.169 --> 01:26:58.170
What's your partner doing here?

1192
01:26:58.171 --> 01:26:59.880
What happened to your eye?

1193
01:26:59.881 --> 01:27:01.381
<font color=#FF551>FRANK:</font> I banged it up.

1194
01:27:01.382 --> 01:27:04.259
Let's go outside and talk. We need to do that.

1195
01:27:04.260 --> 01:27:05.802
- About what?
- Let's go.

1196
01:27:05.803 --> 01:27:07.471
- Do us both a favor.
- All right.

1197
01:27:07.472 --> 01:27:10.614
- Okay.
- All right.

1198
01:27:12.310 --> 01:27:16.161
Stay there. John. I'll be right back.

1199
01:27:16.481 --> 01:27:20.082
I'll be right back. all right?

1200
01:27:31.704 --> 01:27:35.306
So where were you last night. Frank?

1201
01:27:35.833 --> 01:27:39.544
Where do you think I was. Satch?

1202
01:27:39.545 --> 01:27:42.396
Same place I found this.

1203
01:27:43.258 --> 01:27:46.358
Under the body of a dead woman.

1204
01:27:48.179 --> 01:27:52.349
No. no. This isn't what you think. okay?

1205
01:27:52.350 --> 01:27:55.519
- No. this isn't what you think.
- I wanna be wrong here. Frank.

1206
01:27:55.520 --> 01:27:58.730
Let's just take a ride down to
the precinct and talk about it.

1207
01:27:58.731 --> 01:28:01.358
Yeah. I wanna talk to you
too. I need to talk to you.

1208
01:28:01.359 --> 01:28:04.444
- Come on. just take a ride.
- All right. let me just go inside...

1209
01:28:04.445 --> 01:28:08.881
...tell my family where I'm
going. all right? Be right back.

1210
01:28:11.202 --> 01:28:14.386
Everything's all right. Don't worry.

1211
01:28:14.914 --> 01:28:17.874
<font color=#FF551>ANNOUNCER:</font> <font color=#ff00ff>[ON TV]</font> He's
played in 10 World Series.

1212
01:28:17.875 --> 01:28:20.043
They loved him in his town.

1213
01:28:20.044 --> 01:28:21.878
- Chief. Chief. you there?
- Yeah.

1214
01:28:21.879 --> 01:28:24.715
- They found Sissy Clark. They think I did it.
- Frank.

1215
01:28:24.716 --> 01:28:28.468
<i><font color=#FF551>- JULIA:</font> Frank. what's going on?
- Give me a second. You gotta talk to Satch.</i>

1216
01:28:28.469 --> 01:28:30.637
<i><font color=#FF551>- FRANK:</font> Just give me a sec.
- What's going on?</i>

1217
01:28:30.638 --> 01:28:32.389
<i><font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> Uncle Satch. don't.
- Stay with me.</i>

1218
01:28:32.390 --> 01:28:35.225
What's going on? Satch. what's going on?

1219
01:28:35.226 --> 01:28:39.271
I wanna talk to you right
now! You don't understand!

1220
01:28:39.272 --> 01:28:40.480
<font color=#FF551>- SATCH:</font> Come on.
<font color=#FF551>- JOHN:</font> Stop!

1221
01:28:40.481 --> 01:28:43.832
<font color=#ff00ff>[SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]</font>

1222
01:28:45.194 --> 01:28:48.379
Frank. come on!

1223
01:28:49.574 --> 01:28:52.424
<font color=#FF551>JOHN:</font> Stop!

1224
01:29:05.840 --> 01:29:09.525
- He's a cop.
- A cop.

1225
01:29:11.095 --> 01:29:13.347
Jack Shepard.

1226
01:29:13.348 --> 01:29:16.224
He's a detective at the 15th precinct.

1227
01:29:16.225 --> 01:29:17.684
I swear. Satch.

1228
01:29:17.685 --> 01:29:20.312
And you got all of this
from the guy on the radio...

1229
01:29:20.513 --> 01:29:23.598
- ...from your son in the future.
- Yeah. yeah. yeah.

1230
01:29:23.599 --> 01:29:25.475
As nuts as that sounds. yeah.

1231
01:29:25.476 --> 01:29:28.535
Uh-huh.

1232
01:29:30.147 --> 01:29:32.732
You gotta listen to me. You
gotta open up your mind.

1233
01:29:32.733 --> 01:29:34.901
- Try to understand what I'm saying.
- Listen.

1234
01:29:34.902 --> 01:29:38.488
You got something going on with
this girl. that's one thing.

1235
01:29:38.489 --> 01:29:41.632
But you gotta tell me.

1236
01:29:42.493 --> 01:29:45.704
Are you listening to me?
You're in a world of shit.

1237
01:29:45.705 --> 01:29:49.040
An eyewitness put you outside
the dead girl's apartment.

1238
01:29:49.041 --> 01:29:53.086
Your prints are all over the place. not
to mention the goddamn driver's license.

1239
01:29:53.087 --> 01:29:56.006
Now Chuck is getting a search
warrant for your house.

1240
01:29:56.007 --> 01:29:59.426
- What's he gonna find there. Frank. huh?
- Nothing. Nothing.

1241
01:29:59.427 --> 01:30:02.178
You gotta give me something.
something I can believe.

1242
01:30:02.179 --> 01:30:05.265
<font color=#ff00ff>[ANNOUNCER CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY
ON RADIO FROM NEXT ROOM]</font>

1243
01:30:05.266 --> 01:30:07.809
<font color=#ff00ff>[OFFICERS GROANING]</font>

1244
01:30:07.810 --> 01:30:12.955
<font color=#FF551>ANNOUNCER:</font> Seventy-five for Dave McNally.
Two Mets are out in the fifth inning...

1245
01:30:13.232 --> 01:30:18.028
- What if I can prove it to you. huh?
- How's that?

1246
01:30:18.029 --> 01:30:22.240
World Series. Where are they right
now? What. fourth. fifth inning. huh?

1247
01:30:22.241 --> 01:30:24.743
Well. what if I was to tell you...

1248
01:30:24.744 --> 01:30:30.165
...that in the bottom of the sixth inning.
the Mets are gonna be down 3-zip?

1249
01:30:30.166 --> 01:30:32.500
And Cleon Jones. he's gonna come to bat.

1250
01:30:32.501 --> 01:30:38.089
Now. he's gonna get hit in
the foot by a wild pitch.

1251
01:30:38.090 --> 01:30:40.467
It's gonna leave a shoe-polish mark on the ball.

1252
01:30:40.468 --> 01:30:43.053
- Frank...
- Now. listen. Hear me out. all right?

1253
01:30:43.054 --> 01:30:46.473
He goes to first. Clendenon comes up.

1254
01:30:46.474 --> 01:30:49.601
He's gonna hit a 2-2 pitch
into the left field bleachers.

1255
01:30:49.602 --> 01:30:50.810
This is insane. Frank.

1256
01:30:50.811 --> 01:30:55.106
And then in the bottom of the seventh.
Weis is going to hit a solo home run.

1257
01:30:55.107 --> 01:30:57.400
And then Jones and Swoboda score in the eighth.

1258
01:30:57.401 --> 01:30:59.694
The Mets. they're gonna win that game 5-to-3.

1259
01:30:59.695 --> 01:31:01.905
You go watch. If it don't happen. I'm a liar.

1260
01:31:01.906 --> 01:31:05.799
- Go watch the game? Watch the...?
- Yeah. watch the game.

1261
01:31:05.910 --> 01:31:09.829
Frank. they're gonna make
you for Sissy Clark's murder.

1262
01:31:09.830 --> 01:31:12.666
And they're gonna match that
with the Nightingale murders.

1263
01:31:12.667 --> 01:31:14.501
Do you understand what that means?

1264
01:31:15.002 --> 01:31:15.919
<font color=#ff00ff>[KNOCKING ON DOOR]</font>

1265
01:31:15.920 --> 01:31:17.253
Yeah.

1266
01:31:17.254 --> 01:31:19.047
<i><font color=#FF551>MAN:</font> His wife is here.</i>

1267
01:31:19.048 --> 01:31:22.107
<i>She wants to talk to you.</i>

1268
01:31:42.822 --> 01:31:48.592
<i>...ball player from Pittsfield Massachusetts
High School. fouled out of play.</i>

1269
01:31:50.996 --> 01:31:55.125
<i>He has those loose actions in the field.</i>

1270
01:31:55.126 --> 01:31:56.751
<font color=#ff00ff>[SIGHS]</font>

1271
01:31:56.752 --> 01:31:59.879
<i>You can tell he must have been
quite a basketball player.</i>

1272
01:31:59.880 --> 01:32:02.048
<i>One-two pitch to him.</i>

1273
01:32:02.049 --> 01:32:04.175
<i>Fly ball to right.</i>

1274
01:32:04.176 --> 01:32:09.154
- <i>Swoboda waits and there's one down.</i>
- Let's walk. Jules. Get a cup of coffee.

1275
01:32:10.558 --> 01:32:12.100
<i>Dave McNally.</i>

1276
01:32:12.101 --> 01:32:14.853
The guy just went crazy. You know what I mean?

1277
01:32:14.854 --> 01:32:17.605
Started tearing things apart.

1278
01:32:17.606 --> 01:32:21.317
- He was throwing things.
<font color=#FF551>- OFFICER2:</font> Yeah.

1279
01:32:21.318 --> 01:32:22.610
- Hey.
- Hey.

1280
01:32:22.611 --> 01:32:24.988
<font color=#FF551>OFFICER1:</font> <i>So I cuffed him...</i>

1281
01:32:24.989 --> 01:32:26.656
<i><font color=#FF551>MAN:</font> He must be exhausted. I think.</i>

1282
01:32:26.657 --> 01:32:32.954
<font color=#FF551>WOMAN:</font> I know. I talked to them several
times. but they just won't listen.

1283
01:32:32.955 --> 01:32:34.414
- How you doing?
<font color=#FF551>- CLERK:</font> <i>Hey.</i>

1284
01:32:34.615 --> 01:32:37.167
You got a collar in here for
the Nightingale murders?

1285
01:32:37.168 --> 01:32:39.502
- Yeah?
- Yeah. come on in.

1286
